WEBVTT

01:08.610 --> 01:11.454
[ Man ] Your son has
arrived from London, sir.

01:14.825 --> 01:16.748
Father.

01:16.827 --> 01:19.376
John.John-

01:20.831 --> 01:24.085
You will find out soon enough
from my will...

01:24.167 --> 01:27.091
that the estate of Norland
was left to me...

01:27.170 --> 01:30.094
in such a way
as prevents me...

01:30.173 --> 01:33.097
from dividing it
between my two families.

01:33.176 --> 01:35.304
Calm yourself, Father.
This cannot be good for you.

01:35.387 --> 01:38.766
Nofland,
in its entirety,

01:38.849 --> 01:43.104
is therefore yours by law,

01:43.186 --> 01:47.111
and I am happy for you...

01:47.190 --> 01:49.363
and Fanny.

01:50.569 --> 01:52.537
But your stepmother,

01:52.613 --> 01:55.116
my wife and daughters,

01:55.198 --> 01:59.453
are left only £500 a year-
barely enough to live on.

01:59.536 --> 02:02.039
Nothing for the girls' dowries.

02:04.291 --> 02:07.636
You must help them.

02:07.711 --> 02:10.180
O-Of course.

02:10.255 --> 02:13.555
You must promise to do this.

02:15.010 --> 02:17.934
I promise, Father.

02:18.013 --> 02:20.311
I promise.

02:20.390 --> 02:23.985
[Fanny] “Help them”? What
do you mean, “help them”?

02:24.061 --> 02:27.315
Dearest, I mean
to give them £3,000.

02:27.397 --> 02:31.072
The interest will provide them
with a little extra income.

02:31.151 --> 02:35.327
Such a gift will certainly
discharge my promise to my father.

02:35.405 --> 02:37.908
Without question.
More than amply.

02:38.408 --> 02:40.081
One had rather,
on such occasions,

02:40.160 --> 02:43.084
do too much than too little.

02:45.165 --> 02:48.590
Of course he did not
stipulate a particular sum.

02:52.005 --> 02:53.507
[John]
£1,500, then.

02:53.590 --> 02:55.058
What do you say to 1,500?

02:55.133 --> 02:58.512
What brother on earth would do
half so much for his real sisters,

02:58.595 --> 03:00.438
let alone half-blood?

03:00.514 --> 03:02.312
Well, they can hardly
expect more.

03:02.391 --> 03:04.109
There's no knowing
what they expect.

03:04.184 --> 03:06.858
The question is,
what can you afford?

03:06.937 --> 03:09.360
[ Man Shouting ]
[ Hog Snorting ]

03:09.439 --> 03:12.534
[John] A hundred pounds a year to
their mother, while she lives.

03:12.609 --> 03:14.202
Would that be
more advisable?

03:14.277 --> 03:16.951
It is better than parting
with the 1,500 all at once.

03:17.030 --> 03:19.453
But if she should live
longer than 15 years,

03:19.533 --> 03:21.581
we'd be completely
takenin.

03:22.619 --> 03:25.748
People always live forever when there
is an annuity to be paid them.

03:25.831 --> 03:27.799
[ Beating Sound ]

03:29.584 --> 03:32.633
Twenty pounds now and then will amply
discharge my promise, you're quite right.

03:32.713 --> 03:34.636
Indeed.

03:34.715 --> 03:36.888
Although, to say the truth,
l'm convinced within myself...

03:36.967 --> 03:40.016
that your father had no idea
of your giving them money.

03:40.095 --> 03:43.019
They will have 500 a year
amongst them as it is.

03:43.098 --> 03:46.022
And what on earth could four
women want for more than that?

03:46.101 --> 03:48.024
Their housekeeping
will be nothing at all.

03:48.103 --> 03:52.028
They'll have no carriage, no horses, hardly
any servants and will keep no company.

03:52.107 --> 03:54.701
Only conceive
how comfortable they will be.

03:55.569 --> 03:57.913
They will be much more able
to give you something.

04:02.284 --> 04:05.208
N' [ Piano: Melancholy]

04:17.591 --> 04:19.514
N' [ Continues ]

04:21.303 --> 04:24.557
Marianne, can you play something else?
IJ' [ Stops ]

04:24.639 --> 04:27.563
Mama has been weeping
since breakfast.

04:33.774 --> 04:35.776
W: [ Dirge]

04:37.861 --> 04:40.740
I meant something
less mournful, dearest.

04:40.822 --> 04:42.745
N' [ Continues ]

04:42.824 --> 04:46.124
To be reduced to the condition
of visitor in my own home.

04:46.203 --> 04:49.127
It is not to be borne,
Elinor.

04:49.206 --> 04:52.130
Consider, Mama,
we have nowhere to go.

04:52.209 --> 04:54.758
John and Fanny will be descending
from London at any moment.

04:54.836 --> 04:57.089
Do you expect me to
be here to welcome them?

04:57.172 --> 04:58.674
Vultures!

05:00.342 --> 05:02.936
[Sobbing ]

05:03.011 --> 05:04.934
N' [ Continues ]

05:12.395 --> 05:15.820
I will start making inquiries
for a new house at once.

05:18.109 --> 05:21.454
Until then we must try
to bear their coming.

05:24.491 --> 05:27.415
Margaret, are you there?
Please come down.

05:27.494 --> 05:30.418
John and Fanny
will be here soon.

05:31.665 --> 05:34.339
Why are they coming
to live at Norland?

05:34.417 --> 05:37.045
They already have
a house in London.

05:37.128 --> 05:42.100
Because houses go from father to son,
dearest, not from father to daughter.

05:42.175 --> 05:44.098
It is the law.

05:44.177 --> 05:48.102
Uh- If you come inside,
we could play with your atlas.

05:48.181 --> 05:51.685
It's not my atlas anymore.
lt's their atlas.

05:55.230 --> 05:57.153
[All Murmuring ]

05:58.358 --> 06:00.281
Do sit down.

06:01.528 --> 06:04.452
As you know,
we are looking for a new home.

06:04.531 --> 06:08.707
And when we leave we shall be able
to retain only Thomas and Betsy.

06:09.828 --> 06:13.253
We are very sorry
to have to leave you all,

06:13.331 --> 06:16.756
but we are certain that you will
find the new Mrs. Dashwood...

06:16.835 --> 06:19.088
a fair and generous mistress.

06:20.589 --> 06:24.765
[ Fanny] My only real concern is how
long it will take them to move out.

06:46.948 --> 06:48.871
How is Mrs. Ferrars?

06:48.950 --> 06:52.329
My mother is always
in excellent health, thank you.

06:52.412 --> 06:54.961
My brother Robert is
in town with her this season...

06:55.040 --> 06:57.463
and quite the most popular
bachelor in London.

06:57.542 --> 07:00.011
He has his own barouche.

07:00.086 --> 07:02.134
Oh.
[Silverware Clatters]

07:03.173 --> 07:05.596
- [ Sighs ] - You have two
brothers, have you not?

07:05.675 --> 07:09.600
Indeed,yes. Edward is the elder.
Mama quite depends upon him.

07:09.679 --> 07:13.149
He's traveling up from Plymouth shortly
and will break his journey here.

07:18.313 --> 07:21.237
If that is agreeable to you,
of course.

07:21.316 --> 07:23.239
My dear John,

07:24.569 --> 07:26.537
this is your home now.

07:30.408 --> 07:34.333
Fanny wishes to know where the key
to the silver cabinet is kept.

07:34.412 --> 07:37.131
Betsy has it, I think. What does
Fanny want with the silver?

07:37.207 --> 07:40.552
One can only presume
she wants to count it.

07:40.627 --> 07:43.801
What are you doing?
Presents for the servants.

07:43.880 --> 07:46.884
Have you seen Margaret, by the way?
l'm worried about her.

07:46.967 --> 07:50.141
She's taken to hiding in the oddest places.
Fortunate girl.

07:50.220 --> 07:53.224
At least she can escape Fanny,
which is more than any of us is able.

07:53.306 --> 07:56.150
You do your best. You've not
said a word to her for a week.

07:56.226 --> 07:57.694
Ihave.

07:57.769 --> 07:59.737
L've said “yes” and “no.”

08:13.785 --> 08:15.753
Good morning,
Fanny.

08:18.373 --> 08:20.375
Good morning,
Miss Marianne.

08:21.418 --> 08:25.013
How did you find the silver?
VVas it all genuine?

08:25.088 --> 08:29.685
Pray, when may we expect the
pleasure of your brother's company?

08:29.759 --> 08:31.557
Edward is due tomorrow.

08:32.178 --> 08:34.020
Oh, and my dear
Mrs. Dashwood,

08:34.097 --> 08:36.976
in view of the fact that
he will not be with us for long,

08:37.058 --> 08:40.278
I wonder if Miss Margaret will be
prepared to give up her room for him.

08:40.352 --> 08:42.400
The view is quite incomparable
from her windows,

08:42.480 --> 08:46.701
and I should so much like Edward to see
Norland at its best. [ Silverware Clatters ]

08:46.776 --> 08:48.744
[ Hoofbeats
Approaching ]

08:50.447 --> 08:52.370
[ Bleating ]

09:08.548 --> 09:12.974
Mrs. Dashwood, Miss
Dashwood, Miss Marianne,

09:13.053 --> 09:15.181
my brother
Edward Ferrars.

09:16.806 --> 09:18.729
[ Fanny, Mrs. Dashwood ]
Do sit down-

09:22.270 --> 09:24.648
[Fanny]
But where is Miss Margaret?

09:24.731 --> 09:28.531
I declare, Mrs. Dashwood, l'm beginning to doubt
of her existence. She must run positively wild.

09:28.610 --> 09:31.989
Pray, forgive us, Mr. Ferrars. My
youngest is not to be found this morning.

09:32.072 --> 09:34.666
She's a little shy
of strangers at present.

09:35.742 --> 09:37.665
N-N-Naturally.

09:37.744 --> 09:42.420
L'm shy of strangers myself,
and I have nothing like her excuse.

09:42.499 --> 09:45.423
How do you like your view,
Mr. Ferrars?

09:48.004 --> 09:49.927
Very much.

09:50.006 --> 09:53.886
Your stables are very handsome
and beautifully kept, Mrs. Dashwood.

09:53.968 --> 09:57.598
Stables?
Edward, your windows overlook the lake.

09:57.680 --> 10:01.685
A-An oversight, Fanny, had led
me to one of the family rooms,

10:01.768 --> 10:05.113
but l've rectified the situation
and am very happily installed...

10:05.188 --> 10:07.361
in the guest quarters.

10:08.942 --> 10:10.569
Tea.

10:12.362 --> 10:14.785
They're all exceedingly
spoilt, I find.

10:14.864 --> 10:18.960
Miss Margaret spends all her time
up trees and under furniture.

10:19.035 --> 10:22.460
L've barely had a civil word
from Marianne.

10:22.539 --> 10:25.793
My dear Fanny, they've
just lost their father.

10:25.875 --> 10:29.300
Their lives will never
be the same again.

10:29.379 --> 10:31.302
That is no excuse.

10:33.341 --> 10:35.264
[ Door Opens ]

10:35.343 --> 10:37.562
[Fanny]
Library.

10:40.515 --> 10:42.438
These are mostly foreign.

10:43.560 --> 10:46.188
Indeed.
Magnificent.

10:46.271 --> 10:48.365
Never liked the smell of books.

10:48.439 --> 10:52.660
Oh. No, well, it is-
it is the dust, perhaps.

10:53.903 --> 10:56.281
I hear you have great plans
for the walnut grove.

10:56.364 --> 11:00.335
Oh, yes. I shall have it knocked down
to make way for a Grecian temple.

11:00.410 --> 11:03.539
[ Margaret VVhines ] Mmm! That
does sound extremely interesting.

11:03.621 --> 11:05.589
Would you show me
the site?

11:12.589 --> 11:14.557
Too expensive.

11:14.632 --> 11:17.932
And we do not need four bedrooms.
\/Ve can share.

11:19.053 --> 11:20.930
This one then.

11:21.014 --> 11:23.938
Marianne, we have only
£500 a year.

11:25.351 --> 11:29.026
I will send out more inquiries today.
[ Knocking ]

11:32.317 --> 11:35.241
Pardon my intrusion, but, um,

11:35.320 --> 11:39.291
I think I may have found,
uh, what you were looking for.

11:40.575 --> 11:42.498
Oh!

11:43.661 --> 11:45.629
[Whispers ]
Sorry.

11:48.791 --> 11:51.169
Won't you come out,
dearest?

11:51.252 --> 11:53.175
We haven't seen you all day.

11:53.254 --> 11:56.178
[Fanny] So later, of course,
we shall have to enlarge it.

11:56.257 --> 12:00.228
[ Elinor] Mama is very concerned. Oh, and
Mattocks will help you adjust to our hours.

12:00.303 --> 12:01.805
[ Knocking ]

12:02.805 --> 12:05.729
Oh. Miss Dashwood.

12:05.808 --> 12:07.731
Forgive me.

12:07.810 --> 12:11.735
Do you, by any chance, have such
a thing as a reliable atlas?

12:11.814 --> 12:13.441
I believe so.

12:13.524 --> 12:17.074
Excellent. I, uh, wish to check
the position of the Nile.

12:17.153 --> 12:20.783
My sister tells me it is in South America.
[ Margaret Snickers ]

12:21.991 --> 12:23.914
Oh!

12:23.993 --> 12:25.916
No. No.

12:25.995 --> 12:31.422
Um, she's quite wrong, um, for
I believe it is in Belgium.

12:31.501 --> 12:34.596
Belgium.
Oh, surely not, I-

12:34.671 --> 12:37.424
I think you must be thinking
of the Volga. The Volga?

12:37.507 --> 12:42.729
Of course. The Volga, which, as you know,
starts in- Vladivostok, and ends in-

12:42.804 --> 12:45.933
Wimbledon. Precisely. VVhere
the coffee beans come from.

12:46.015 --> 12:50.862
[ Scoffs ] The source of
the Nile is in Abyssinia!

12:50.937 --> 12:52.860
Is it?

12:54.315 --> 12:56.738
How interesting.
How do you do?

12:56.818 --> 12:59.412
Edward Ferrars.
Margaret Dashwood.

12:59.487 --> 13:01.740
Delighted to make
your acquaintance.

13:01.823 --> 13:03.746
It immediately adjoins this property.
Quite so?

13:03.825 --> 13:06.749
It cannot be but a most
desirable addition.

13:06.828 --> 13:10.253
I will ride there tomorrow
and speak to- who is it?

13:10.331 --> 13:12.254
Gibson.
Gibson.

13:12.333 --> 13:15.052
He ought to be pleased
to sell, no doubt.

13:15.128 --> 13:19.053
[ Fanny] He will certainly ask for more
than it is worth. Do not be too eager.

13:19.132 --> 13:21.305
No, no,
you're quite right.

13:21.384 --> 13:24.479
[ Margaret Shouting ] [ Fanny ] V\/e have
no desire to lose it to somebody else.

13:24.554 --> 13:29.151
L'll go tomorrow as planned.
[Fanny] Merely inquire.

13:29.225 --> 13:31.819
[ Margaret ] Like this?
[ Edward ] Yes.

13:31.894 --> 13:34.317
[John] After all, there'll
be few enough offers.

13:34.397 --> 13:36.900
The land thereabout is marshy.
[ Together ] Lunge!

13:36.983 --> 13:39.486
[ Sticks Banging Together]
[ Margaret ] Here!

13:39.569 --> 13:43.790
[ Grunting ] [ Fanny] lt's possible
we may get some assistance from Mama.

13:43.865 --> 13:47.745
She mentioned in her letter
a gift she made to Robert.

13:47.827 --> 13:50.751
- Oh! Ooh. - [ Margaret]
Did I hurt you?

13:50.830 --> 13:52.798
[ Groans ]
Oh. No, no.

13:52.874 --> 13:55.297
[ John, Fanny Continue,
lndistinct ]

13:57.754 --> 14:00.257
N' [ Piano: Melancholy]

14:26.657 --> 14:29.126
N' [ Continues ]

14:44.384 --> 14:46.728
[ Sniffles ]

14:51.849 --> 14:54.477
[ Sniffles ]

14:54.560 --> 14:56.983
Thank you.
Forgive me.

14:58.856 --> 15:01.325
That was
my father's favorite.

15:04.695 --> 15:06.197
No-

15:06.280 --> 15:08.908
Thank you so much for your help
with Margaret, Mr. Ferrars.

15:08.991 --> 15:11.414
She's quite changed
since you came.

15:11.494 --> 15:14.418
Not at all.
I enjoy her company.

15:14.497 --> 15:17.421
Has she shown you the tree house?
Not yet.

15:18.668 --> 15:20.591
W-Would-

15:20.670 --> 15:22.843
Would you do me the honor,
Miss Dashwood?

15:24.173 --> 15:26.596
It is very fine out.

15:26.676 --> 15:28.770
With pleasure.

15:28.845 --> 15:30.347
N' [ Continues ]

15:30.430 --> 15:33.104
[ Elinor] Margaret has
always wanted to travel.

15:33.182 --> 15:35.605
I know. She's heading an
expedition to China shortly.

15:35.685 --> 15:37.278
I am to go
as her servant,

15:37.353 --> 15:39.947
but only on the understanding
that I will be very badly treated.

15:40.022 --> 15:41.615
[ Elinor Laughs ]

15:41.691 --> 15:43.614
What will your duties be?

15:43.693 --> 15:45.616
Sword fighting,
obviously,

15:45.695 --> 15:47.618
administering rum
and... swabbing.

15:47.697 --> 15:51.292
[Laughs] Which of those duties
will take precedence for you?

15:51.367 --> 15:53.495
The swabbing,
I would imagine.

15:53.578 --> 15:56.957
[ Elinor, Edward Continue,
lndistinct ]

15:57.039 --> 15:58.757
[ Elinor Laughs ]

15:59.792 --> 16:02.011
All I want-

16:02.086 --> 16:04.714
All I have ever wanted is
the quiet of a private life.

16:04.797 --> 16:07.721
But, uh, my mother is determined
to see me distinguished.

16:07.800 --> 16:09.973
As?
AnYthing_

16:10.052 --> 16:13.477
Um, a great orator,
a leading politician.

16:13.556 --> 16:16.901
I think even a barrister would serve,
as long as I drove a barouche...

16:16.976 --> 16:18.478
and dined in the first circle.

16:18.561 --> 16:20.484
What do you wish for?

16:21.814 --> 16:24.237
L've always preferred the church.

16:24.317 --> 16:27.696
But that is not smart enough for my mother.
She prefers the army.

16:27.778 --> 16:31.282
But that is a great deal too smart for me.
[ Chuckles ]

16:31.365 --> 16:34.369
Would you stay in London?
I hate London.

16:34.452 --> 16:37.752
No peace.
Uh, country living is my ideal.

16:37.830 --> 16:40.754
A small parish
where I might do some good,

16:40.833 --> 16:43.757
keep chickens,
give very short sermons.

16:43.836 --> 16:45.759
[Chuckling ]

16:49.509 --> 16:52.433
[ Elinor] You talk of
feeling idle and useless.

16:52.512 --> 16:55.812
Imagine how that is compounded
when one has no hope...

16:55.890 --> 16:59.485
and no choice of any
occupation whatsoever.

17:01.103 --> 17:04.073
Our circumstances are,
therefore, precisely the same.

17:05.608 --> 17:08.578
Except that you will
inherit your fortune.

17:10.946 --> 17:12.915
W6 cannot GVGH earn OUFS.

17:15.284 --> 17:17.877
Perhaps Margaret is right.
Right?

17:17.954 --> 17:20.924
Piracy is our only option.
[ Chuckles ]

17:23.209 --> 17:26.053
What is swabbing, exactly?
[Laughs]

17:26.796 --> 17:29.049
[ Edward ] “No voice
divine the storm allayed,

17:29.131 --> 17:31.054
no light propitious shone.

17:31.133 --> 17:33.306
When snatched
from all effectual aid...

17:33.386 --> 17:36.230
we perished-
perished each alone.

17:36.305 --> 17:38.979
But I beneath a rougher sea...

17:39.058 --> 17:42.483
and whelmed
in deeper gulfs than he.”

17:42.562 --> 17:44.530
No, Edward, listen.

17:44.605 --> 17:47.358
[ Passionately ] No voice
divine the storm allayed,

17:47.441 --> 17:50.069
no light propitious shone.

17:50.152 --> 17:52.246
When snatched
from all effectual aid...

17:52.321 --> 17:54.369
we perished, each alone.

17:54.448 --> 17:56.917
Can you not feel
his despair?

17:56.993 --> 17:59.746
[ Sighs ]
Try again.

18:04.709 --> 18:07.588
“No voice divine the
storm allayed- Divine-

18:07.670 --> 18:11.174
Light... propitious shone.
no light propitious shone.

18:11.257 --> 18:14.181
VVhen snatched from all effectual
<i>aid-</i> Snatched from all effectual-

18:14.260 --> 18:17.059
we perished, each alone.”
We perished, each alone.

18:19.432 --> 18:21.355
[ Marianne ]
Mama!

18:24.645 --> 18:27.649
Look.
This has just arrived.

18:29.191 --> 18:32.616
“L should be pleased to offer
you a home at Barton Cottage...

18:32.695 --> 18:35.118
as soon as ever
you have need.”

18:35.197 --> 18:37.291
lt's from my cousin,
Sir John Middleton.

18:37.366 --> 18:39.619
Even Elinor
must approve the rent.

18:39.702 --> 18:42.626
Has Elinor not yet seen this?
No. I will fetch her.

18:42.705 --> 18:45.629
Wait. No.
Let us delay.

18:45.708 --> 18:47.426
Why?

18:47.501 --> 18:50.505
I think-
I believe that...

18:50.588 --> 18:53.512
Edward and Elinor
have formed an attachment.

18:53.591 --> 18:57.471
It would be cruel to take her away so soon.
Devonshire is so far.

18:59.013 --> 19:02.187
V\/hy so grave? Do you
disapprove her choice?

19:02.266 --> 19:04.189
By no means.

19:04.268 --> 19:06.521
Edward is very amiable.

19:06.604 --> 19:09.528
Amiable? But?

19:09.607 --> 19:12.030
But there is something wanting.

19:12.109 --> 19:15.534
He's too sedate.
His reading last night-

19:15.613 --> 19:18.958
But Elinor has not your feelings.
His reserve suits her.

19:19.033 --> 19:20.956
Can he love her?

19:21.035 --> 19:24.835
Can the soul really be satisfied
with such polite affections?

19:24.914 --> 19:27.838
To love is to burn,
to be on fire,

19:27.917 --> 19:30.420
like Juliet
or Guinevere or Eloise.

19:30.503 --> 19:33.632
They met rather pathetic ends, dear.
Pathetic?

19:33.714 --> 19:35.216
To die for love?

19:35.299 --> 19:37.768
How can you say so?
What could be more glorious?

19:37.843 --> 19:41.643
I think that may be taking your
romantic sensibilities a little far.

19:41.722 --> 19:44.271
[ Both Laughing ]

19:46.102 --> 19:48.025
[ Door Opens ]

19:48.104 --> 19:51.654
“Is love a fancy
or a feeling?

19:51.732 --> 19:55.578
No, it is immorial
as immaculate truth.

19:55.653 --> 19:59.874
'Tis not a blossom shed as soon as
youth drops from the stem of life,

19:59.949 --> 20:03.579
for it will grow in barren
regions where no waters flow...

20:03.661 --> 20:06.881
nor ray of promise
cheats the pensive gloom.”

20:06.956 --> 20:08.879
Hmm?

20:10.292 --> 20:12.841
V\/hat a pity it is that Edward
has no passion for reading.

20:12.920 --> 20:16.049
It was you who asked him to read,
then you made him nervous.

20:16.132 --> 20:18.100
Me?
Yes.

20:19.051 --> 20:22.851
But since your behavior to him in all
other respects is perfectly cordial,

20:22.930 --> 20:26.730
I must assume that you like him
in spite of his deficiencies.

20:26.809 --> 20:30.029
I think him... everything...

20:30.104 --> 20:32.527
that is amiable and worthy.

20:33.899 --> 20:36.573
Praise indeed.

20:36.652 --> 20:41.579
But he shall have my unswerving devotion when
you tell me that he is to be my brother.

20:41.657 --> 20:44.877
How shall I do
without you?

20:44.952 --> 20:48.673
Do without me? l'm sure
you will be very happy.

20:48.748 --> 20:51.672
But you must promise not
to live too far away.

20:51.751 --> 20:54.595
Marianne, there is no question
of- That is, there is-

20:54.670 --> 20:57.014
There is no understanding.

20:57.089 --> 20:59.012
Do you love him?

21:00.176 --> 21:02.099
Uh-

21:02.178 --> 21:06.433
