VVe're so happy that you chose
to invite Edward to Norland.

22:16.085 --> 22:19.510
He's a dear boy.
We're all very fond of him.

22:19.588 --> 22:21.511
We have great hopes
for him.

22:21.590 --> 22:24.935
Much is expected of him by our mother
with regard to his profession.

22:25.010 --> 22:27.934
Naturally.
And in marriage.

22:28.013 --> 22:30.937
She's determined that both he
and Robert will marry well.

22:31.016 --> 22:35.647
Of course. But I hope she
desires them to marry for love.

22:36.772 --> 22:39.070
[Fanny]
Love is all very well, but...

22:39.149 --> 22:41.698
unfortunately we cannot
always rely on the heart...

22:41.777 --> 22:44.075
to lead us in the most
suitable directions.

22:45.155 --> 22:47.328
You see,
my dear Mrs. Dashwood,

22:47.408 --> 22:50.332
Edward is entirely the kind
of compassionate person...

22:50.411 --> 22:52.709
upon whom
penniless women can prey.

22:52.788 --> 22:55.541
And having entered
into any understanding,

22:55.624 --> 22:57.672
he would never
go back on his word.

22:57.751 --> 23:00.174
He's simply incapable
of doing so.

23:00.254 --> 23:02.677
But it would lead
to his ruin.

23:03.507 --> 23:05.305
I worry for him so,
Mrs. Dashwood.

23:05.384 --> 23:07.136
My mother has always
made it perfectly plain...

23:07.219 --> 23:09.563
that she would withdraw
all financial support from Edward...

23:09.638 --> 23:11.686
should he choose
to plant his affections...

23:11.765 --> 23:15.190
in less... exalted ground
than he deserves.

23:17.813 --> 23:19.941
I understand you
perfectly.

23:25.154 --> 23:28.749
To Devonshire? My cousin,
Sir John Middleton,

23:28.824 --> 23:31.168
has offered us
a small house on his estate.

23:31.243 --> 23:33.712
[John]
Sir John Middleton?

23:33.787 --> 23:36.415
V\/hat is his situation? He
must be a man of some property?

23:36.498 --> 23:39.843
He is a widower. He lives with his
mother-in-law at Barton Park.

23:39.919 --> 23:43.093
- It is Barton Cottage that he offers us.
- Oh, a cottage.

23:43.172 --> 23:46.096
How charming. A little
cottage is always very snug.

23:46.175 --> 23:48.428
But- Uh-

23:48.510 --> 23:51.104
Y-You will not leave
before the summer.

23:51.180 --> 23:54.104
My dear Edward, we can no longer
trespass upon your sister's good will.

23:54.183 --> 23:56.732
We must leave
as soon as possible.

23:56.810 --> 24:01.532
- You will come and stay with us, Edward?
- I should like that very much.

24:01.607 --> 24:04.281
Edward has long been expected
in town by our mother.

24:04.360 --> 24:06.909
[ Mrs. Dashwood ] Come as
soon as you can, Edward.

24:06.987 --> 24:09.957
Remember,
you're always welcome.

24:19.541 --> 24:21.464
[Whispering ]

24:36.892 --> 24:38.815
Cannot you
take him with you?

24:38.894 --> 24:41.192
We cannot possibly
afford him.

24:43.107 --> 24:45.826
Then perhaps he can make
himself useful in the kitchen.

24:47.111 --> 24:49.079
Forgive me.

24:52.825 --> 24:54.748
Miss Dashwood-

24:57.413 --> 24:59.381
Elinor-

25:00.582 --> 25:02.550
I must speak to you.

25:06.964 --> 25:11.094
There is something of great importance
that I need to, uh...

25:12.720 --> 25:15.348
t-tell you...

25:15.431 --> 25:18.401
about my, uh, education.

25:21.729 --> 25:23.652
Your education?

25:23.731 --> 25:25.859
Yes.

25:25.941 --> 25:28.694
It was conducted, um,

25:28.777 --> 25:31.496
oddly enough, in Plymouth.

25:33.157 --> 25:35.876
- Indeed.
- Yes. Do you know it?

25:35.951 --> 25:37.294
- Plymouth?
- Yes.

25:37.369 --> 25:40.498
- No.
- Oh. Well-

25:41.582 --> 25:44.051
I was four years there,
um-

25:44.126 --> 25:47.630
in a school, uh,
r-run by Mr. Pratt.

25:52.176 --> 25:54.053
Pratt?
Precisely, yes.

25:54.136 --> 25:57.606
Pratt. And, uh...

25:57.681 --> 25:59.900
while I was there-

25:59.975 --> 26:02.854
That is to say,
he ha- he had a-

26:02.936 --> 26:04.483
has a, um-

26:04.563 --> 26:07.032
[Fanny]
Edward! Edward!

26:07.816 --> 26:10.114
[Panfing] Edward, l've
been all over for you.

26:10.194 --> 26:12.071
You're needed in London
this instant.

26:12.154 --> 26:15.704
L'm leaving this afternoon as it is.
No, no, that will not do.

26:15.783 --> 26:18.707
Mama is quite adamant
you should leave at once.

26:20.704 --> 26:22.627
Excuse me.

26:55.072 --> 26:59.077
- Edward promised he'd bring the
atlas to Barton for me. - Did he?

27:00.953 --> 27:04.674
Well, <i>l'll</i> wager he will do so
in less than a fortnight.

27:05.666 --> 27:07.885
Dear Edward.

27:28.647 --> 27:32.322
[ Man ] Hello there, now! Welcome!
[Woman ] Mrs. Dashwood!

27:32.401 --> 27:34.824
Welcome, you poor creatures!
Yoo-hoo!

27:34.903 --> 27:38.282
There! Do you see? Just as I tell you.
There they are!

27:38.365 --> 27:40.959
Sir John. [Woman ]
Oh, how very kind.

27:41.034 --> 27:44.379
[ Dogs VVhining, Barking ]
[Sir John, Woman Chattering ]

27:47.207 --> 27:50.632
Here- Here we are! Dear ladies!
Dear ladies!

27:50.711 --> 27:54.306
Upon my word,
here ye are, here ye are!

27:54.381 --> 27:58.431
Oh, Sir John, your extraordinary
kindness- Oh, no, none of that!

27:58.510 --> 28:00.433
Hush, please.
None of that.

28:00.512 --> 28:04.483
But here is my dear mama-in-law, Mrs.
Jennings. [ Barking Continues ]

28:04.558 --> 28:08.153
Now get down, dogs! This
must be Miss Dashwood.

28:08.228 --> 28:10.777
Was your journey tolerable?
Oh, you poor souls!

28:10.856 --> 28:14.281
VVhy did ye not come up to the
Park first and take her in?

28:14.359 --> 28:18.284
VVe saw you pass. Oh, I could
not wait for you to come to us!

28:18.363 --> 28:20.786
I made John call a carriage!
Get down, you dog!

28:20.866 --> 28:23.460
She would not wait, you know.
VVe've had so little company!

28:23.535 --> 28:27.790
[ Laughing ] Ah, but I feel
as if I know you already.

28:27.873 --> 28:30.296
Delightful creatures! Are
they not delightful?

28:30.375 --> 28:33.629
[ Sir John ] And you know you must
dine at Barton Park every day.

28:33.712 --> 28:36.807
[ Mrs. Dashwood ] Oh, my dear Sir John,
we cannot possibly. No,no,no,no,no!

28:36.882 --> 28:40.307
I would not brook refusals.
l'm quite deaf to them, you know?

28:40.385 --> 28:43.309
[ Mrs. Jennings Laughs ] Deaf to them!
But I insist!

28:43.388 --> 28:47.484
[ Elinor] Let us settle in for a few days,
but thank you so very much. No, no.

28:47.559 --> 28:49.903
[ Sir John ]
No thanks, I beg you.

28:49.978 --> 28:52.902
I could not bear it. [ Mrs. Dashwood, Mrs.
Jennings Laughing ]

28:52.981 --> 28:54.858
[ Dogs Barking ]

28:54.942 --> 28:56.865
[ Mrs. Jennings]
I declare!

28:56.944 --> 28:59.868
They are the loveliest
girls I ever set eyes on!

28:59.947 --> 29:02.871
Can you not get them married, Mrs.
Dashwood?

29:02.950 --> 29:04.873
You must not leave it
any longer.

29:04.952 --> 29:08.377
[ Sir John ] Alas, there are no smart
young men here about to woo them.

29:08.455 --> 29:12.380
[ Mrs. Jennings] Not a beau for miles.
Come, Mama, Let us leave them in peace.

29:12.459 --> 29:16.054
And send your man up to us for the
carriage as soon as you're ready!

29:16.129 --> 29:18.348
Good-bye. [ Elinor] Thank you!

29:18.423 --> 29:21.848
No, don't thank us! Good day to you!
Oh, good-bye!

29:21.927 --> 29:24.021
[ Murmuring ]
Oh, here you are!

29:24.096 --> 29:27.020
Come on, boys. Come on.
Come along.

29:27.099 --> 29:30.023
[Shivering ]

29:41.154 --> 29:43.077
Your feet are cold.

30:08.557 --> 30:10.480
[ Marianne ]
What have you been doing?

30:10.559 --> 30:13.483
Your neck is so dirty
you could grow a potato on it.

30:13.562 --> 30:17.442
[Gasps]
lt's cold. l'm cold.

30:17.524 --> 30:19.447
Hot. Thank you, Elinor.

30:19.526 --> 30:21.449
It's hot.

30:23.572 --> 30:26.496
[ Marianne ] How do you
manage it, Margaret?

30:26.575 --> 30:28.498
[Chattering ]

30:28.577 --> 30:30.500
[ Sir John ]
Where can Brandon be?

30:30.579 --> 30:33.503
Poor fellow. I hope he's
not lamed his horse.

30:33.582 --> 30:36.927
Colonel Brandon is the most
eligible bachelor in the county.

30:37.002 --> 30:39.505
[Sir John ] Yes, indeed. He's
bound to do for one of you.

30:39.588 --> 30:43.183
- [ Chuckling ] - Mind, I think he's
a better age for Miss Dashwood.

30:43.258 --> 30:45.010
[Sir John Laughs]

30:45.093 --> 30:48.267
But I dare say, she's left her
heart behind in Sussex, hmm?

30:48.347 --> 30:52.227
- [Sir John Chuckles] Oh-ho-ho!
- I see you, Miss Marianne.

30:52.309 --> 30:54.687
I think
l've unearthed a secret.

30:54.770 --> 30:57.694
Sniffed one out already? You're worse
than my best pointer, Flossie!

30:59.358 --> 31:02.032
What sort of man is he,
Miss Dashwood?

31:02.110 --> 31:05.205
Butcher? Baker?
Candlestick maker?

31:05.280 --> 31:08.955
- I shall winkle it out of you, you know.
- She's horribly good at winkling.

31:09.034 --> 31:13.210
You're in lonely country now, Miss Dashwood.
VVe none of us have any secrets here.

31:13.288 --> 31:17.714
- Or if we do, we do not keep them long.
- [ Mrs. Jennings Laughing ]

31:17.793 --> 31:22.549
- He's curate of the parish, I dare say.
- Or perhaps a handsome lieutenant.

31:22.631 --> 31:26.807
- Give us a clue, Miss Dashwood. ls he
in uniform? - He has no profession.

31:26.885 --> 31:29.388
- Oh. - [ Sir John
] No profession.

31:29.471 --> 31:31.394
Uh, he's a gentleman, then.

31:31.473 --> 31:35.853
Margaret, you know perfectly
well there is no such person.

31:35.936 --> 31:39.190
There is! There is, and
his name begins with an

31:39.272 --> 31:42.651
- Margaret! - Oh?
- An “F” indeed!

31:42.734 --> 31:46.329
- There's a promising letter. “F,” “For!
- Uh, Foster?

31:46.405 --> 31:49.249
- There's one!
- Uh, Forrest? Fotheringay?

31:49.324 --> 31:52.544
- Foggarty?
- Oh, yes, l- l- Fortescue!

31:52.619 --> 31:55.088
- Fondant?
- [ Both Laughing ]

31:55.163 --> 31:59.589
Sir John, might I play
your pianoforte?

31:59.668 --> 32:02.512
Yes, yes, of course.

32:02.587 --> 32:04.260
My goodness.

32:04.339 --> 32:07.559
Yes, we do not stand
upon ceremony here, my dear.

32:07.634 --> 32:09.557
[ Mrs. Dashwood ] Sir
John, please forgive her.

32:09.636 --> 32:11.559
[ Mrs. Jennings ] An entertainment!
I declare!

32:11.638 --> 32:14.767
