34:00.455 --> 34:03.959
- What's it like?
- Like? Hot.

34:04.042 --> 34:06.841
The air is full of spices.

34:06.920 --> 34:09.547
- [All Chuckling ] - [ Mrs.
Jennings ] How lovely.

34:09.630 --> 34:12.635
Now, Miss Dashwood,
it's your turn to entertain us.

34:12.717 --> 34:15.391
Oh, no, Sir John,
I don't-

34:15.469 --> 34:19.190
And I believe I know
what key you will sing in:

34:19.266 --> 34:21.188
F Major.

34:21.268 --> 34:25.364
[ Snickering,
Laughing Continues]

34:34.406 --> 34:38.581
And as for you, you have no right to
parade your ignorant assumptions-

34:38.659 --> 34:41.163
They're not assumptions.
You told me.

34:42.664 --> 34:46.714
I told you nothing. They'll
meet him when he comes anyway.

34:46.793 --> 34:50.422
Margaret, that is not the point. You do not
speak of such things before strangers.

34:50.505 --> 34:54.179
But everyone else was. Mrs.
Jennings is not everyone.

34:54.259 --> 34:57.354
I like her.
She talks about things.

34:57.429 --> 35:00.729
VVe never talk about things. [ Mrs.
Dashwood ] Hush, please.

35:00.807 --> 35:02.730
That is enough,
Margaret.

35:02.809 --> 35:07.360
If you cannot think of anything appropriate to say,
you will please restrict your remarks to the weather.

35:10.483 --> 35:13.908
Surely they've got enough reeds
for a Moses basket by now.

35:13.987 --> 35:16.115
[ Margaret]
Mama! We've got lots!

35:18.908 --> 35:22.128
Wrap your string around this.
Good and tight.

35:22.203 --> 35:24.581
[ Margaret]
I know tight.

35:27.208 --> 35:28.881
[ Sighs ]

35:52.567 --> 35:55.446
[ Sir John ] You know what
they're saying, of course.

35:55.528 --> 35:57.451
Hmm?

35:57.530 --> 36:01.205
V\/ord is, you've developed a
taste for certain company.

36:01.284 --> 36:03.207
And why not, say I?

36:03.286 --> 36:05.709
A man like you
in his prime?

36:05.789 --> 36:08.212
She'd be a very fortunate
younglady.

36:08.291 --> 36:12.216
Marianne Dashwood would no more think
of me than she would of you, John.

36:12.295 --> 36:15.219
Brandon, my boy, do not think
of yourself so meanly.

36:15.298 --> 36:17.767
And all the better for her.

36:33.441 --> 36:35.443
[ Brandon ] Very good.
[ Dog Barks ]

36:35.527 --> 36:37.450
[ Marianne ]
Oh, Casper.

36:37.529 --> 36:39.577
[ Margaret]
No, Casper!

36:41.866 --> 36:43.789
Oh, no.
Oh!

36:43.868 --> 36:45.791
Oh!

36:45.870 --> 36:48.043
Besofied.
[Chucmes]

36:48.123 --> 36:50.046
An excellent match.

36:50.125 --> 36:52.298
For he's rich
and she's handsome.

36:52.377 --> 36:54.721
How long have you
known the colonel?

36:54.796 --> 36:57.970
Oh, Lord bless you, as long
as ever l've been here,

36:58.049 --> 37:00.472
and I came
15 years back.

37:00.552 --> 37:05.479
His estate at Delaford is but four miles
hence, and he and John are very thick.

37:05.557 --> 37:08.731
He has no wife and children,
for he-

37:08.810 --> 37:10.733
he had a tragic history.

37:10.812 --> 37:14.737
He loved a girl once,
2O years ago now.

37:14.816 --> 37:17.865
A ward to his family.
But they were not permitted to marry.

37:17.944 --> 37:21.494
- On what grounds?
- Money. Eliza was poor.

37:21.573 --> 37:23.826
When the father
discovered their <i>amour,</i>

37:23.908 --> 37:27.253
she was flung out of the house and
he was packed up into the army.

37:27.328 --> 37:30.298
I think he would've
done himself a harm if not for John.

37:31.416 --> 37:34.386
What became of the lady?
[ Sighs ]

37:34.461 --> 37:37.385
She was passed from man to man.
[ Casper Barks ]

37:37.464 --> 37:39.683
Disappeared from all good society.

37:39.758 --> 37:42.682
[ Laughing ] When Brandon
came back from India,

37:42.761 --> 37:44.855
he searched
heaven knows how long,

37:44.929 --> 37:48.274
only to find her dying
in a poorhouse.

37:48.349 --> 37:51.899
Once I thought my daughter
Charlotte might've cheered him up.

37:51.978 --> 37:54.731
But she's better off where she is.
[ Chuckles ]

37:54.814 --> 37:57.533
But look at him now.

37:57.609 --> 38:01.079
So attentive.
[ Chuckling ]

38:01.154 --> 38:04.704
[Sir John ] VVell done! I think I
shall try a little experiment on him.

38:04.783 --> 38:07.787
Oh, no. Mrs. Jennings,
please leave the poor colonel alone.

38:07.869 --> 38:11.749
No, no, my dear. lt'sjust the thing.
All suitors need a little help.

38:11.831 --> 38:13.754
[Laughs]
Colonel Brandon!

38:13.833 --> 38:16.757
We have not heard you
play for us of late.

38:16.836 --> 38:20.136
There's a simple reason, that you
have a far superior musician here.

38:20.215 --> 38:24.470
Perhaps you did not know, Miss Marianne, that
our dear Brandon shares your passion for music.

38:24.552 --> 38:27.726
He plays a pianoforte
very well.

38:27.806 --> 38:29.729
Oh, come.

38:29.808 --> 38:34.609
I trow you know as many melancholy
tunes as Miss Marianne.

38:34.687 --> 38:36.610
You must play us a duet!

38:36.689 --> 38:40.239
Let us see you both
side by side.

38:40.318 --> 38:42.821
I do not know any duets.

38:42.904 --> 38:44.872
Forgive me, Colonel.

38:46.241 --> 38:48.164
[ Mrs. Jennings Chuckles]

38:50.245 --> 38:53.715
Oh, are we never
to have a moment's peace?

38:53.790 --> 38:57.010
The rent here may be low, but I believe
we have it on very hard terms.

38:57.085 --> 39:00.009
Mrs. Jennings is a wealthy
woman with a married daughter.

39:00.088 --> 39:03.012
She has nothing to do
but marry off everyone else's.

39:03.091 --> 39:05.435
There's a parcel arrived for you, Mrs.
Dashwood.

39:05.510 --> 39:07.433
[ Elinor] A parcel? Ch, lOOk!

39:07.512 --> 39:10.436
V\/hen did it arrive? While
you were up at the Park.

39:10.515 --> 39:12.859
Can I open it?
It is too ridiculous.

39:12.934 --> 39:16.689
V\/hen is a man to be safe from such wit,
if age and infirmity do not protect him?

39:16.771 --> 39:19.866
- Infirmity? - If Colonel Brandon is
infirm, then I am at death's door.

39:19.941 --> 39:22.319
It is a miracle your life
has extended this far.

39:22.402 --> 39:24.871
Did you not hear him complain
of a rheumatism in his shoulder?

39:24.946 --> 39:27.540
[ Elinor] “A slight ache”
I believe was his phrase.

39:32.579 --> 39:36.459
But Edward said
he would bring it himself.

39:38.710 --> 39:42.556
“Dear Mrs. Dashwood, Miss Dashwood,
Miss Marianne and Captain Margaret,

39:42.630 --> 39:46.351
it gives me great pleasure to restore
this atlas to its rightful owner.

39:46.426 --> 39:49.896
Alas, business in London does
not permit me to accompany it,

39:49.971 --> 39:52.895
although this is likely to hurt
me far more than it hurts you.

39:52.974 --> 39:56.399
For the present my memories of your
kindness must be enough to sustain me...

39:56.477 --> 40:00.607
and I remain your devoted
servant always, E.C. Ferrars.”

40:01.608 --> 40:03.781
Why hasn't he come?

40:03.860 --> 40:05.658
He says he's busy,
dean

40:05.737 --> 40:08.786
[ Margaret] He said he'd come.
VVhy hasn't he come?

40:08.865 --> 40:12.165
[ Marianne ] l'm taking you for a walk.
No, l've been a walk.

40:12.243 --> 40:14.291
You need another.
lt's going to rain.

40:14.370 --> 40:18.466
It is not going to rain. You always
say that and then it always does.

40:19.667 --> 40:22.637
I fear Mrs. Jennings
is a bad influence.

40:30.011 --> 40:31.979
You must miss him,
Elinor.

40:33.306 --> 40:35.274
We are not engaged,
Mama.

40:37.018 --> 40:40.522
But he loves you, dearest.
Of that I am certain.

40:40.605 --> 40:43.404
I am, by no means, assured of
his regard for me. Oh, Elinor-

40:43.483 --> 40:45.531
But even were he to feel
such a preference,

40:45.610 --> 40:49.535
I think we should be foolish to assume
that there would not be many obstacles...

40:49.614 --> 40:54.040
to his marrying a- a woman of no
rank who cannot afford to buy sugar.

40:54.118 --> 40:56.541
But, Elinor,
your heart must tell you-

40:56.621 --> 41:00.046
In such a situation, Mama, it is
perhaps better to use one's head.

41:08.716 --> 41:10.639
This can't be
good for me.

41:10.718 --> 41:13.642
It's very good for you.
Stop complaining.

41:13.721 --> 41:16.645
It's giving me a cough. It
is not' giving you a cough.

41:16.724 --> 41:18.647
Please,
can we go back?

41:18.726 --> 41:21.650
It's lovely. Come on.
Catch up! Catch up!

41:21.729 --> 41:23.982
[ Groans ]

41:24.065 --> 41:25.988
Justover that fence-
[Thunder Rumbling ]

41:26.067 --> 41:27.990
There's a field
full of rabbits.

41:28.069 --> 41:30.413
I don't want to see rabbits.
Yes, you do.

41:35.368 --> 41:38.998
[ Sighs ] ls there any felicity
in the world superior to this?

41:39.080 --> 41:42.926
I told you it would rain! There's
some blue sky! Let us chase it!

41:43.418 --> 41:45.261
L'm not supposed to run.

41:48.006 --> 41:49.929
Aaah!
Marianne!

41:50.008 --> 41:52.431
[Grunting, Groaning ]
Are you hurt?

41:52.510 --> 41:54.433
Aaah!

41:54.512 --> 41:56.435
[Thunder Rumbling ]

41:56.514 --> 41:59.188
Margaret, I do not
think I can walk.

41:59.267 --> 42:02.612
You must run and fetch help. [
Murmurs] I will run as fast as I can.

42:09.694 --> 42:12.322
[ Hoofbeats Pounding ]

42:12.405 --> 42:15.534
- Margaret!
- [ Hoofbeats Continue]

42:15.616 --> 42:18.039
- Margaret!
- [ Screams ]

42:18.119 --> 42:21.840
- [ Horse Whinnies ]
- [ Panting ]

42:21.914 --> 42:26.511
[ Thunder Continues ] Don't be afraid.
He's quite safe.

42:31.174 --> 42:34.348
- Are you hurt?
- Only my ankle.

42:35.511 --> 42:38.685
May I have your permission
to ascertain if there are any breaks?

42:43.019 --> 42:45.317
[Whimpers ]

42:49.150 --> 42:51.073
[Whimpering ]

42:51.152 --> 42:53.905
[ Panting ]

42:58.993 --> 43:01.246
It is not broken.

43:01.329 --> 43:04.674
Now, can you put your arm
about my neck?

43:04.749 --> 43:06.672
[ Panting Continues,
Gasps ]

43:08.336 --> 43:10.759
Allow me
to escort you home.

43:15.802 --> 43:17.725
[ Door Opens ]
At last.

43:18.805 --> 43:21.684
She fell over! She fell
down and he's carrying her!

43:21.766 --> 43:23.268
What?
[ Panting ]

43:24.644 --> 43:27.614
Marianne, are you all right? [ Mrs.
Dashwood ] Oh, my darling.

43:27.688 --> 43:29.611
[ Man ]
lt's a twisted ankle.

43:29.690 --> 43:32.614
Do not be alarmed, Mama. I can
assure you it's not serious.

43:32.693 --> 43:35.788
I took the liberty of feeling the
bone and it's perfectly sound.

43:35.863 --> 43:38.787
Sir, I cannot even begin to thank you.
Please do not think of it.

43:38.866 --> 43:41.085
I am honored
to be of service.

43:41.160 --> 43:45.461
- V\/ill you not be seated? - Excuse me,
I have no desire to leave a watermark.

43:45.540 --> 43:49.465
But permit me to call tomorrow afternoon
and inquire after the patient?

43:49.544 --> 43:51.763
We sh- We shall
look forward to it.

43:51.838 --> 43:54.682
You're most kind. Thank you.
l'll show you out.

43:56.676 --> 43:59.850
Margaret, give the gentleman his hat.
Thank you.

44:01.472 --> 44:04.646
- [ Whispering ] His name! His name!
- Oh, his name.

44:04.725 --> 44:07.695
Please, could you tell us to
whom we are so much obliged?

44:07.770 --> 44:10.740
John VVilloughby of Allenham,
at your service, ma'am.

44:10.815 --> 44:14.194
John Willoughby
of Allenham.

44:16.320 --> 44:18.539
What an impressive gentleman.

44:19.407 --> 44:22.456
He lifted me as if I weighed
no more than a dried leaf.

44:22.535 --> 44:24.663
Is he human?
[ Laughing ]

44:24.745 --> 44:27.168
Tell me if I hurt you.

44:27.248 --> 44:29.751
She feels no pain,
Mama.

44:29.834 --> 44:33.930
Margaret, ask Betsy to make up a cold
compress, please, quickly as you can.

44:34.005 --> 44:37.430
Oh, please don't say anything important.
Go on, go on.

44:37.508 --> 44:39.306
Betsy!
Did you see him?

44:39.385 --> 44:40.978
He expressed himself well,
did he not?

44:41.053 --> 44:44.307
VVith great decorum and honor.
And spirit and wit and feeling.

44:44.390 --> 44:47.485
- And economy. Ten words at most.
- [ Margaret] VVait for me!

44:47.560 --> 44:50.939
- And he is to come tomorrow. - Marianne,
you must change. You will catch a cold.

44:51.022 --> 44:53.275
What care I for colds
when there is such a man?

44:53.357 --> 44:55.530
You will care very much
when your nose swells up.

44:55.610 --> 44:57.612
You are right.
Help me, Elinor.

44:57.695 --> 44:59.197
[ Groans ]

45:00.615 --> 45:03.368
[ Sir John ] Mr. VVilloughby's well
worth catching, Miss Dashwood.

45:03.451 --> 45:06.876
Miss Marianne must not expect
to have all the men to herself.

45:06.954 --> 45:10.925
- But what do you know of Mr.
Vvilloughby, Sir John? - Decent shot.

45:11.000 --> 45:14.800
- And there's not a bolder rider in
all England. - But what is he like?

45:14.879 --> 45:18.725
- “Like”? - What are his tastes,
his passions, his pursuits?

45:20.218 --> 45:22.141
Well,

45:22.220 --> 45:25.724
he has the smartest
little bitch of a pointer.

45:25.806 --> 45:29.356
- V\/as she out with him yesterday?
- Where is Allenham, Sir John?

45:29.435 --> 45:31.984
Allenham? Nice little
estate three miles east.

45:32.063 --> 45:35.067
He's to inherit it
from an elderly relative.

45:35.149 --> 45:38.119
Lady Allen's the name.
[ Dogs Barking ]

45:43.449 --> 45:47.704
It's Colonel Brandon. I shall
go outside and keep watch.

45:48.788 --> 45:50.586
Hello, Colonel!

45:50.665 --> 45:53.919
You're all on the lookout for
VVilloughby, eh? Dear me, poor Brandon.

45:54.001 --> 45:56.424
You will none of you
think of him now?

45:56.504 --> 45:58.427
[ Elinor]
Come in.

45:59.674 --> 46:02.644
[ Mrs. Dashwood ] Colonel. [ Sir
John ] Good morning, Brandon.

46:02.718 --> 46:06.313
Good morning.
How's the invalid?

46:06.389 --> 46:08.767
Oh, thank you so much,
Colonel.

46:08.849 --> 46:11.227
Uh, Elinor, would
you- Miss Marianne,

46:11.310 --> 46:13.904
I cannot think why you should
set your cap atvvmoughbyu.

46:13.980 --> 46:17.154
When you've already made
such a splendid conquest.

46:17.233 --> 46:20.533
I have no intention of setting
my cap at anyone, Sir John.

46:20.611 --> 46:23.114
Mr. Willoughby,
Lady Allen's nephew?

46:23.197 --> 46:25.620
Aye, he visits every year,
for he's to inherit.

46:25.700 --> 46:31.127
Um, and he has a very pretty estate
of his own, you know, Miss Dashwood.

46:31.205 --> 46:33.958
Combe Magna in Somerset.

46:34.041 --> 46:38.296
Aye, if I were you I would not
give him up to a younger sister...

46:38.379 --> 46:40.473
for all this
tumbling downhill.

46:40.548 --> 46:42.721
- [ Margaret ] Marianne's preserver!
- Don't run.

46:42.800 --> 46:45.098
Ah, ah, the man himself.

46:45.177 --> 46:50.604
Come, Brandon. Vve know when we are not
wanted. Let us leave him to the ladies.

46:50.683 --> 46:52.981
Thank you so much
for calling.

46:55.271 --> 46:58.696
Marianne, the colonel
and Sir John are leaving.

46:58.774 --> 47:01.903
Good-bye, Sir John. Colonel,
thank you for the flowers.

47:03.529 --> 47:05.452
[ Dogs Barking ]

47:05.531 --> 47:08.034
[ Sir John Muttering,
indistinct ]

47:13.289 --> 47:17.214
How do you do, Colonel? How does he do?
How do you do, more like.

47:17.293 --> 47:20.217
Go on in.
They're waiting for you.

47:20.296 --> 47:22.219
Come on, Briar!

47:22.298 --> 47:24.221
Come on.

47:24.300 --> 47:26.268
[Sir John Shouting ]

47:28.429 --> 47:31.148
[ Elinor] Good day, Mr. V\/illoughby.
[ Chuckles ]

47:31.223 --> 47:33.146
[Whispers ]
Stop it.

47:33.225 --> 47:35.603
Stop it.

47:36.687 --> 47:38.610
Mr. Willoughby.

47:38.689 --> 47:41.989
What a pleasure
to see you again.

47:42.068 --> 47:43.741
The pleasure is all mine,
I can assure you.

47:43.819 --> 47:45.537
I trust Miss Marianne
has not caught cold?

47:45.613 --> 47:48.537
You found out my name.
But of course.

47:48.616 --> 47:51.540
- The neighborhood is crawling
with my spies. - [ Women Chuckle ]

47:51.619 --> 47:54.498
And since you cannot
venture out to nature,

47:54.580 --> 47:57.003
nature must be
brought to you.

47:57.083 --> 48:00.883
Oh, how beautiful.
These are not from the hothouse.

48:02.129 --> 48:05.053
Ah, I see mine is not
the first offering,

48:05.132 --> 48:07.055
nor the most elegant.

48:07.134 --> 48:09.683
I obtained those
from an obliging field.

48:09.762 --> 48:11.685
L've always preferred wildflowers.

48:11.764 --> 48:13.892
I suspected as much.

48:13.974 --> 48:16.443
Elinor, would you put these in
water, please? Oh, yes. Excuse me.

48:16.519 --> 48:19.443
Our gratitude is beyond expression.
But it is I who am grateful.

48:19.522 --> 48:23.527
L've often passed this cottage and
grieved for its lonely state.

48:23.609 --> 48:27.079
Then the first news I had from Lady Allen
when I arrived was that it was taken.

48:27.154 --> 48:30.579
I felt a peculiar interest in the event
which nothing can account for...

48:30.658 --> 48:33.502
but my present delight in meeting you.
[Whispering ]

48:33.577 --> 48:35.545
Pray, sit down, Mr. VVilloughby.
Thank you.

48:35.621 --> 48:38.249
Ah, who is reading
Shakespeare's sonnets?

48:38.332 --> 48:39.834
I am.
We all are.

48:39.917 --> 48:41.919
[All Chuckling 1

48:42.002 --> 48:46.098
Marianne is reading them out to us.
Which are your favorites?

48:46.173 --> 48:49.643
Oh- VVithout a
doubt, mine is 116.

48:49.718 --> 48:53.768
Let me not to the marriage of
true minds admit impediments.

48:53.848 --> 48:57.318
Love is not love
which alters when it alteration finds...

48:57.393 --> 49:00.237
or bends with the remover to remove.

49:01.439 --> 49:03.362
Then how does it continue?

49:03.441 --> 49:07.036
Oh, no! lt is an ever-fixed
mark- It is an ever-fixed mark-

49:07.111 --> 49:09.455
- that looks on storms- -
that looks on tempests- Oh!

49:09.530 --> 49:12.625
- L-ls it “tempests”?
- I do believe it is “tempests.”

49:12.700 --> 49:14.794
Let me find it.
[Whispers ]

49:14.869 --> 49:18.464
It's strange you should be reading these,
for look, I carry them with me always.

49:18.539 --> 49:21.167
[ Gasps ]
Oh, how beautiful.

49:22.293 --> 49:24.216
[ Laughing, Chattering ]

49:30.134 --> 49:32.057
Until tomorrow then.

49:36.348 --> 49:38.942
And my pocket sonnets
are yours, Miss Marianne,

49:39.018 --> 49:41.646
a talisman
against further injury.

49:41.729 --> 49:44.733
Good-bye.
Thank you.

49:49.987 --> 49:52.911
Good work, Marianne.

49:52.990 --> 49:55.914
You've covered Shakespeare,
Scott, all forms of poetry.

49:55.993 --> 49:59.418
Another meeting will ascertain his views
on nature and romantic attachments.

49:59.497 --> 50:03.422
Then you will have nothing left to talk
about and the relationship will be over.

50:03.501 --> 50:05.469
I suppose I have erred
against decorum.

50:05.544 --> 50:09.924
I should've been dull and spiritless and talked
only of the weather or the state of the roads.

50:10.007 --> 50:13.932
No, but Mr. VVilloughby can be in no
doubt of your enthusiasm for him.

50:14.011 --> 50:17.436
VVhy should he doubt it? VVhy
should I hide my regard?

50:17.515 --> 50:20.940
No particular reason. Only
that we know so little of him.

50:21.018 --> 50:23.441
Time alone does not
determine intimacy.

50:23.521 --> 50:26.946
Seven years would be insufficient to make
some people acquainted with each other,

50:27.024 --> 50:30.949
and seven days can be more than enough for
others. Or seven hours, in this case.

50:31.028 --> 50:33.451
I feel I know
Mr. Willoughby already.

50:33.531 --> 50:35.454
If I had more
shallow feelings,

50:35.533 --> 50:38.958
I could, perhaps, conceal them as you do.
Marianne, that is not fair.

50:39.036 --> 50:42.461
L'm sorry, Elinor. I did not mean-
Do not trouble yourself, Marianne.

50:42.540 --> 50:45.464
[Sighs] [ Footsteps
Ascending Stairs ]

50:47.044 --> 50:49.547
I do not understand her,
Mama.

51:07.982 --> 51:10.986
[ Mrs. Jennings Chattering ]

51:16.657 --> 51:18.625
[Chattering Continues]

51:18.701 --> 51:21.500
[Willoughby Whispering ]
Marianne.

51:23.247 --> 51:25.170
Haven't you finished yet?

51:25.249 --> 51:28.378
No. Patience.

51:33.340 --> 51:35.513
[ Chuckles ]

51:39.680 --> 51:43.651
Surely you're not going to
deny us beef as well as sugar.

51:43.726 --> 51:47.651
There is nothing under 1O pence a
pound, Mama. V\le have to economize.

51:47.730 --> 51:50.654
No. Do you want us to starve?

51:50.733 --> 51:52.656
Just not to eat beef.

51:52.735 --> 51:55.204
[Willoughby Whispering ]

51:57.031 --> 51:59.033
[Whispering Continues]

52:05.039 --> 52:08.009
[Whispering ]
Hmm? This one here?

52:12.296 --> 52:14.298
[ Indistinct 1

52:19.803 --> 52:22.727
[ Marianne ] Vvmoughby,
slow down for the corner!

52:22.806 --> 52:25.730
[ Marianne Screaming ] Careful!
You'll run someone down!

52:25.809 --> 52:27.732
[Screaming Continues]
[ Shouting ]

52:30.856 --> 52:32.779
[ BOY]
Did you see that?

52:32.858 --> 52:35.782
[ Horse VVhinnies ] I do think
they'll be married before long.

52:35.861 --> 52:40.116
If there was any true impropriety in my
behavior, I should be sensible of it, Elinor.

52:40.199 --> 52:44.124
But it has already exposed you to
some very impertinent remarks.

52:44.203 --> 52:46.422
Do you not begin to doubt
your own discretion?

52:47.539 --> 52:50.964
If the impertinent remarks of such as Mrs.
Jennings are proof of impropriety,

52:51.043 --> 52:53.341
then we are all offending every
moment of our lives. [ Murmuring ]

52:53.420 --> 52:55.764
[ Brandon ] Good morning!
Good morning, Colonel!

52:58.592 --> 53:01.971
Miss Dashwood.
Miss Marianne.

53:02.054 --> 53:05.024
I come to issue
aninvfiafion.

53:07.976 --> 53:11.401
A picnic on my estate
at Delaford,

53:11.480 --> 53:15.826
if you would care to join us,
on Thursday next.

53:15.901 --> 53:18.996
[ Carriage Approaching ] Mrs.
Jennings' daughter and her husband...

53:19.071 --> 53:21.165
are traveling up especially.

53:23.367 --> 53:26.337
We should be delighted,
Colonel.

53:26.412 --> 53:31.543
[ Carriage Approaching ] I will, of course,
be including Mr. Vvilloughby in the party.

53:32.793 --> 53:35.717
I should be delighted
to join you, Colonel.

53:41.093 --> 53:43.016
Good morning,
Miss Dashwood.

53:43.095 --> 53:45.518
Good morning, Colonel. Good morning, Mr.
VVilloughby.

53:45.597 --> 53:49.022
The colonel has invited us to
Delaford, VVilloughby. Excellent.

53:49.101 --> 53:52.105
I understand you have a particularly
fine pianoforte, Colonel.

53:52.187 --> 53:54.736
A Broadwood Grand. [ Marianne
] A Broadwood Grand?

53:54.815 --> 53:58.319
Then I shall really be able to play for
you all. VVe shall look forward to it.

53:58.402 --> 54:00.621
Good day.
Walk on. Walk on.

54:01.655 --> 54:03.623
Good-bye.

54:13.167 --> 54:15.386
Your sister seems very happy.

54:15.461 --> 54:17.384
Yes.

54:17.463 --> 54:20.387
Marianne does not approve
of hiding her emotions.

54:21.675 --> 54:23.598
In fact,
her romantic prejudices...

54:23.677 --> 54:26.772
have the unfortunate tendency
to set propriety at naught.

54:26.847 --> 54:29.566
She is wholly unspoilt.

54:29.641 --> 54:32.235
Rather too unspoilt
in my view.

54:32.311 --> 54:36.236
The sooner she becomes acquainted with
the ways of the world, the better.

54:41.195 --> 54:44.119
I knew a lady very like your sister-

54:44.198 --> 54:47.122
the same impulsive sweetness of temper-

54:47.201 --> 54:51.502
who was forced into, as you put it, a
better acquaintance with the world.

54:52.664 --> 54:56.089
The result was only
ruination and despair.

54:58.670 --> 55:01.093
Do not desire it,
Miss Dashwood.

55:04.968 --> 55:08.142
[ Sir John ] Colonel Brandon's lawn
is perfect for kite launching.

55:08.222 --> 55:11.442
We must have your sky kite.
Mind them pretty ribbons.

55:11.517 --> 55:12.985
John, set that in there!

55:13.060 --> 55:15.404
[ Chuckling,
Murmuring ]

55:15.479 --> 55:17.402
Imagine my surprise,
Mrs. Dashwood,

55:17.481 --> 55:20.655
when Charlotte and her lord and
master appeared with our cousin Lucy.

55:20.734 --> 55:23.704
The last person
I expected to see!

55:23.779 --> 55:25.907
She probably came
to join in the fun,

55:25.989 --> 55:29.414
for there are no funds for such
luxuries at home, poor thing.

55:29.493 --> 55:32.918
L'd not seen you for so long, dear Mrs.
Jennings, I couldn't resist the opportunity.

55:32.996 --> 55:37.172
You sly thing! It was the Misses Dashwood
she wanted to see, not Delaford, Mama.

55:37.251 --> 55:40.221
I have heard nothing but “Miss
Dashwood this, Miss Dashwood that”...

55:40.295 --> 55:42.013
for I don't know how long.

55:42.089 --> 55:44.683
And what do you think of them
now you do see them, Lucy?

55:44.758 --> 55:48.604
My mother has talked of nothing else in
her letters since you came to Barton.

55:48.679 --> 55:52.024
Mr. Palmer, are they not the very
creatures she describes? Nothing like.

55:52.099 --> 55:55.023
[ Mrs. Jennings Laughs] Mr.
Palmer, you are quite rude today.

55:55.102 --> 55:57.355
He's to be an MP,
Mrs. Dashwood.

55:57.437 --> 56:00.782
It is very fatiguing for him for he
is forced to make everybody like him.

56:00.858 --> 56:03.862
He says it is quite shocking. I
never said anything so irrational.

56:03.944 --> 56:06.663
[ Mrs. Jennings ] Oh, Mr.
Palmer's so droll.

56:06.738 --> 56:08.661
He's always out of humor.

56:08.740 --> 56:10.458
Oh! Here he comes.

56:10.534 --> 56:13.458
Now you shall see, Charlotte.
[ Dogs Barking ]

56:17.457 --> 56:19.710
VVhoa.VVhoa.

56:19.793 --> 56:22.342
Hello,
Mr. Willoughby!

56:22.421 --> 56:26.051
Come, you must meet my daughter Charlotte.
Mr. Palmer.

56:26.133 --> 56:30.479
- How do you do?
- And our little cousin, Miss Lucy Steele.

56:30.554 --> 56:32.977
Welcome to our party,
Miss Steele.

56:33.056 --> 56:35.229
Turn about. Come 'round, boys.
Come 'round.

56:35.309 --> 56:39.439
[ Mrs. Jennings ] I know Mr.
VVilloughby extremely well.

56:39.521 --> 56:42.866
May I beg a seat beside you,
Miss Dashwood?

56:42.941 --> 56:45.069
L've so longed to make
your better acquaintance.

56:45.152 --> 56:49.658
- L've heard nothing but the highest
praise of you. - I would be delighted.

56:49.740 --> 56:53.165
But Sir John and Mrs. Jennings are
too excessive in their compliments.

56:53.243 --> 56:55.086
Oh, no.
I am sure to disappoint.

56:55.162 --> 56:58.086
No, for it was from quite
another source I heard you praised,

56:58.165 --> 57:00.884
and one not at all inclined
to exaggeration.

57:00.959 --> 57:03.007
[ Charlotte Giggling ] [ Sir
John ] VVhat can this be?

57:08.675 --> 57:11.349
[ Dogs Barking ]

57:14.097 --> 57:16.270
Is Colonel Brandon here?
Over here!

57:16.350 --> 57:18.023
Where is he?
There he is!

57:26.026 --> 57:28.529
My horse. Quickly!

57:28.612 --> 57:31.616
- What's the matter, Brandon?
- I must away to London.

57:31.698 --> 57:34.542
- No! Impossible!
- Imperative!

57:34.618 --> 57:37.417
But w-we're all assembled!
Hlsend for my things later.

57:37.496 --> 57:40.420
VVe cannot picnic at Delaford without
our host. Go up to town tomorrow.

57:40.499 --> 57:43.469
Or wait until we return and start then.
You'd not be six hours later.

57:43.543 --> 57:46.592
[ Horse VVhinnies] I cannot
afford to lose one minute.

57:46.672 --> 57:48.595
Forgive me.

57:48.674 --> 57:52.269
I hope it's nothing serious, Colonel.
[ Hoofbeats ]

57:52.344 --> 57:56.315
[Sir John] Upon my soul, this is all
very unusual! [ Guests Chattering ]

57:58.850 --> 58:01.854
Frailty, thy name is Brandon.

58:02.479 --> 58:05.153
[ Marianne ] There are some people
who can't bear a party of pleasure.

58:05.232 --> 58:09.738
You're a very wicked pair. Colonel
Brandon will be sadly missed.

58:09.820 --> 58:14.451
V\/hy? When he is the sort of man
that everyone speaks well of...

58:14.533 --> 58:16.956
and no one remembers to talk to.
[ Marianne ] Exactly.

58:17.035 --> 58:20.380
[ Mrs. Dashwood ] Nonsense. Colonel Brandon
is very highly respected at Barton Park.

58:20.455 --> 58:22.674
Hmph. Which is enough
censure in itself, hmm?

58:22.749 --> 58:24.877
Really, Willoughby.

58:24.960 --> 58:27.884
[ Imitating Mrs. Jennings ]
Come, come, Mr. lmpudence.

58:27.963 --> 58:30.887
I know you and your wicked ways.
Oh! [Giggling ]

58:30.966 --> 58:33.890
Come, Miss Dashwood. Reveal your beau.
Reveal him, I say.

58:33.969 --> 58:36.893
Let's have no secrets between friends.
Let me winkle them out of you.

58:36.972 --> 58:40.192
Hush. I do declare,
Miss Marianne.

58:40.267 --> 58:42.861
If I do not have you married
to the colonel by teatime,

58:42.936 --> 58:45.359
I shall swallow
my own bonnet.

58:45.439 --> 58:47.362
As if you could marry
such a character.

58:48.275 --> 58:50.323
Why should you dislike him?

58:51.820 --> 58:55.040
Because he has threatened rne
with rain when I wanted it fine.

58:55.115 --> 58:56.867
[ Mrs. Dashwood Chuckles]

58:56.950 --> 58:59.669
He has found fault
with the balance of my high flyer.

58:59.745 --> 59:02.874
And I cannot persuade him
to buy my brown mare. Ch!

59:02.956 --> 59:05.379
If it will be of any satisfaction
to you, however,

59:05.459 --> 59:08.053
to be told that I believe his character
to be, in all other respects...

59:08.128 --> 59:11.553
irreproachable, then l'm ready to
confess it. [ Marianne Squealing ]

59:11.631 --> 59:14.680
And in return for such an acknowledgment
that must give me some pain-

59:14.760 --> 59:17.559
Aaah! you cannot deny
me the privilege...

59:17.637 --> 59:20.561
of disliking him
as much as I adore...

59:25.729 --> 59:27.652
this cottage.

59:29.900 --> 59:32.699
I have great plans for improvements
to it, you know, Mr. Vvilloughby.

59:32.778 --> 59:36.408
Now, that I will
never consent to.

59:36.490 --> 59:38.959
Not a stone must be
added to its walls.

59:40.869 --> 59:43.588
Were I rich enough, I would
instantly pull down Combe Magna...

59:43.663 --> 59:46.132
and rebuild it
in the exact image of this cottage.

59:46.208 --> 59:50.384
V\/ith dark narrow stairs, a poky hall
and a fire that smokes, I suppose.

59:50.462 --> 59:53.011
Especially the fire
that smokes.

59:53.090 --> 59:56.515
For then I should be as happy at
Combe as I have been at Barton.

59:58.345 --> 01:00:01.975
But this place has one claim on my affections
that none other can possibly share.

01:00:04.142 --> 01:00:07.646
[ Sighs ] Promise me
you'll neverchangeit

01:00:12.526 --> 01:00:15.120
l'm honored that so fair
and virtuous a lady...

01:00:15.195 --> 01:00:19.291
should compromise her honor by
seeing me to the gate unaccompanied.

01:00:19.366 --> 01:00:22.119
[Laughs] That is exactly
what Elinor would say.

01:00:22.202 --> 01:00:25.172
And she would be right.

01:00:25.247 --> 01:00:29.127
Miss Marianne, will you do me the honor
of granting me an interview tomorrow...

01:00:29.209 --> 01:00:30.677
alone?

01:00:30.752 --> 01:00:33.301
Oh, Willoughby,
we're always alone.

01:00:33.380 --> 01:00:35.633
But there is-

01:00:35.715 --> 01:00:38.468
There's something very particular
I should like to ask you.

01:00:40.053 --> 01:00:43.057
Of course.

01:00:43.140 --> 01:00:46.360
I shall ask Mama
if I may stay behind from church.

01:00:47.602 --> 01:00:49.570
Thank you.

01:00:51.064 --> 01:00:53.192
Until tomorrow, then.

01:00:55.944 --> 01:00:57.912
Miss Marianne.

01:01:08.248 --> 01:01:10.592
Oh, virtue.

01:01:10.667 --> 01:01:14.547
Silently and with fear,
enter thou into the hearts...

01:01:14.629 --> 01:01:16.757
of all them
that hear me this day.

01:01:16.840 --> 01:01:19.263
Do you think he'll kneel
down when he asks her? Shh!

01:01:19.342 --> 01:01:22.937
The fear of him is the beginning of wisdom.
They always kneel down.

01:01:23.013 --> 01:01:26.108
Good understanding have
all they that do thereafter.

01:01:26.183 --> 01:01:29.187
Margaret, Margaret,
come back.

01:01:29.269 --> 01:01:31.442
Splendid sermon!
Splendid.

01:01:31.521 --> 01:01:33.944
[ Marianne Sobbing ]
Oh, no!

01:01:38.195 --> 01:01:41.290
What is wrong, dearest?

01:01:41.364 --> 01:01:44.789
Vvmoughby,
what is the matter?

01:01:44.868 --> 01:01:47.337
I must-

01:01:47.412 --> 01:01:51.383
Forgive me, Mrs. Dashwood.
l'm sent-

01:01:51.458 --> 01:01:55.884
That is to say, Lady Allen has
exercised the privilege of riches...

01:01:55.962 --> 01:01:59.057
upon a dependent cousin
and is sending me to London.

01:01:59.132 --> 01:02:02.887
- When? This morning?
- Almost this moment.

01:02:02.969 --> 01:02:04.892
What a disappointment.

01:02:04.971 --> 01:02:07.895
But your business will not detain
you from us for long, I hope?

01:02:07.974 --> 01:02:10.898
You're very kind, but...

01:02:10.977 --> 01:02:15.107
I have no idea of returning
immediately into Devonshire.

01:02:15.190 --> 01:02:17.909
L'm seldom invited to Allenham
more than once a year.

01:02:17.984 --> 01:02:21.363
Oh, for shame, VVilloughby. Can you wait
for an invitation from Barton Cottage?

01:02:23.240 --> 01:02:26.210
My engagements at present
are of such a n-nature-

01:02:27.619 --> 01:02:31.123
That is to say,
I dare not flatter my-

01:02:31.206 --> 01:02:33.550
It is folly to linger
in this manner.

01:02:33.625 --> 01:02:36.048
I will not torment myself further.

01:02:36.127 --> 01:02:39.757
[Sobbing Continues]
Willoughby, come back!

01:02:39.839 --> 01:02:44.345
Margaret, ask Betsy to make a
cup of hot tea for Marianne.

01:02:44.427 --> 01:02:47.556
What is wrong, my love?
Do not ask me questions.

01:02:47.639 --> 01:02:51.143
- [ Margaret ] Betsy!
- Please let me be!

01:02:53.520 --> 01:02:55.443
[Sobbing Continues]

01:02:55.522 --> 01:02:58.867
[ Door Closes ] They
must have quarreled.

01:02:58.942 --> 01:03:01.070
On, that is unlikely.

01:03:02.445 --> 01:03:04.368
Perhaps this Lady Allen...

01:03:04.447 --> 01:03:07.371
disapproves of his regard
for Marianne...

01:03:07.450 --> 01:03:09.623
and has invented an excuse
to send him away.

01:03:09.703 --> 01:03:12.707
Then why did he not
say as much?

01:03:12.789 --> 01:03:15.633
It is not like Willoughby
to be secretive.

01:03:15.709 --> 01:03:18.428
VVhat is it you suspect him of?
I can hardly tell you.

01:03:18.503 --> 01:03:22.224
But why was his manner so guilty?
What are you saying, Elinor?

01:03:22.299 --> 01:03:25.143
That he's been acting a part to
your sister for all this time?

01:03:25.218 --> 01:03:27.220
No. He loves her.
l'm sure.

01:03:27.304 --> 01:03:30.148
Of course he loves her.

01:03:30.223 --> 01:03:33.898
Has he left her with any assurance
of his return? [ Margaret] Marianne!

01:03:33.977 --> 01:03:38.323
Cannot you ask her if he has proposed?
Certainly not.

01:03:38.398 --> 01:03:42.278
I cannot force a confidence from
Marianne and nor should you.

01:03:42.360 --> 01:03:45.785
V\/e must trust her to confide
in us in her own time.

01:03:47.741 --> 01:03:51.371
There was something so underhand
in the manner of his leaving.

01:03:51.453 --> 01:03:54.548
You are resolved, then, to think the
worst of him? l'm not resolved.

01:03:54.622 --> 01:03:57.171
I prefer to give him the benefit
of my good opinion.

01:03:57.250 --> 01:03:59.469
He deserves no less
from all of us!

01:04:00.295 --> 01:04:03.424
Mama, I am very fond
of Willoughby.

01:04:03.506 --> 01:04:06.885
Mama. Mama.
[ Sobbing ]

01:04:06.968 --> 01:04:10.268
[ Marianne Sobbing ]

01:04:11.556 --> 01:04:14.105
She would not let me in.

01:04:14.184 --> 01:04:17.529
[Sobbing ]

01:04:17.604 --> 01:04:21.950
[All Sobbing ]

01:04:29.657 --> 01:04:32.285
[Sobbing Continues]

01:04:45.632 --> 01:04:48.636
[Chattering Quietly]

01:04:51.137 --> 01:04:54.482
To sail us up
the river.

01:04:54.557 --> 01:04:57.231
[ Margaret ] How will
we travel onland?

01:04:57.310 --> 01:04:59.904
Oh!
Oh!

01:04:59.979 --> 01:05:04.530
- Oh, if only this rain would stop.
- lf only you would stop.

01:05:04.609 --> 01:05:08.830
Oh! [ Laughing ] 'Twas you who
took her off my hands, Mr. Palmer.

01:05:08.905 --> 01:05:11.875
And a very good bargain
you made of it too.

01:05:11.950 --> 01:05:15.580
And now I have the whip hand over
you, for you cannot give her back.

01:05:15.662 --> 01:05:18.290
[Charlotte Laughing ]

01:05:19.499 --> 01:05:22.378
[ Mrs. Jennings] Miss Marianne,
come and play a round with us.

01:05:22.460 --> 01:05:25.384
Looking out at the weather
will not bring him back.

01:05:25.463 --> 01:05:29.263
She ate nothing at dinner. Mind, we're
all a little forlorn these days.

01:05:29.342 --> 01:05:31.970
[ Mrs. Jennings ] London has
swallowed all our company.

01:05:32.053 --> 01:05:37.435
Dear Miss Dashwood, perhaps now
we might have our... discussion.

01:05:37.517 --> 01:05:39.440
Our discussion?

01:05:39.519 --> 01:05:42.648
There is a particular question
l've long wanted to ask you.

01:05:42.730 --> 01:05:45.859
But perhaps you'll think me impertinent?
I cannot imagine so.

01:05:45.942 --> 01:05:47.865
But it is an odd question.
Oh, forgive me.

01:05:47.944 --> 01:05:50.367
I have no wish to trouble you.
No, my dear Miss Steele.

01:05:50.447 --> 01:05:53.041
Miss Dashwood, if only Mr. VVilloughby
had gone home to Combe Magna,

01:05:53.116 --> 01:05:56.370
we could have taken Miss Marianne to see
him. VVe live but half a mile away.

01:05:56.453 --> 01:05:58.000
Five and a half.

01:05:58.079 --> 01:06:02.084
No. I cannot believe it is that far, for you
can see the place from the top of our hill.

01:06:02.167 --> 01:06:05.137
Is it really five and a half?
No. I cannot believe it.

01:06:05.211 --> 01:06:07.839
<i>TTY"</i>

01:06:08.548 --> 01:06:12.553
You have my permission to ask any manner
of question, if that is of any help.

01:06:12.635 --> 01:06:15.058
Thank you.

01:06:15.138 --> 01:06:19.018
I wonder, are you at all acquainted
with your sister-in-law's mother?

01:06:19.100 --> 01:06:21.478
Mrs. Ferrars?

01:06:21.561 --> 01:06:24.064
With Fanny's mother?

01:06:24.147 --> 01:06:27.492
No, I-
I have never met her.

01:06:27.567 --> 01:06:30.662
You must think me strange
for inquiring.

01:06:30.737 --> 01:06:34.162
[Women Chattering ]
If only I dared tell it.

01:06:34.240 --> 01:06:37.995
Lucy, if she tells you
aught of the famous Mr. F,

01:06:38.077 --> 01:06:40.375
you must pass it on.
[ Giggling ]

01:06:42.332 --> 01:06:44.755
Will you take a turn
with me, Miss Dashwood?

01:06:44.834 --> 01:06:46.757
Of course.

01:06:50.089 --> 01:06:52.512
I, uh- I had no idea...

01:06:52.592 --> 01:06:56.438
that you were at all connected
with that family. Oh!

01:06:56.513 --> 01:07:00.017
[Lucy] I am certainly nothing to Mrs.
Ferrars at present,

01:07:00.099 --> 01:07:02.773
but the time may come...

01:07:02.852 --> 01:07:06.948
when we may be very
intimately connected.

01:07:07.774 --> 01:07:09.742
What do you mean?

01:07:12.779 --> 01:07:14.702
Do you have an underst-

01:07:14.781 --> 01:07:17.455
[ Whispering ] Do you have an understanding
with Fanny's brother Robert?

01:07:17.534 --> 01:07:19.536
The youngest?

01:07:19.619 --> 01:07:22.293
No. I never met him in my life.

01:07:22.372 --> 01:07:25.296
No. With Edward.

01:07:26.459 --> 01:07:29.508
Edward? Edward Ferrars?

01:07:29.587 --> 01:07:33.262
Edward and I have
been secretly engaged...

01:07:33.341 --> 01:07:35.844
these five years.

01:07:39.389 --> 01:07:42.233
Oh, you may well
be surprised.

01:07:42.308 --> 01:07:47.235
I should never have mentioned it had I not known
I could entirely trust you to keep our secret.

01:07:47.313 --> 01:07:52.490
Edward would not mind my telling you for I
know he looks on you quite as his own sister.

01:07:55.154 --> 01:07:58.829
L'm sorry.
We- Surely, we-

01:07:59.993 --> 01:08:04.749
We- We surely do not mean
the same Mr. Ferrars.

01:08:04.831 --> 01:08:06.754
Oh, the very same.

01:08:06.833 --> 01:08:11.430
He was four years under the tutelage of
my uncle, Mr. Pratt, down in Plymouth.

01:08:11.504 --> 01:08:13.802
Has he never spoken
of it?

01:08:13.881 --> 01:08:17.602
Yes.
Yes, I believe he has.

01:08:20.179 --> 01:08:24.184
I was very unwilling to enter into it
without his mother's approval.

01:08:24.267 --> 01:08:27.191
But we loved each other
with too great a passion for prudence.

01:08:28.563 --> 01:08:31.442
Though you do not know him
as well as I, Miss Dashwood,

01:08:31.524 --> 01:08:36.826
you must have seen how capable he is of
making a woman sincerely attached to him.

01:08:39.032 --> 01:08:43.037
I cannot pretend it has not
been very hard on us both.

01:08:43.118 --> 01:08:46.589
We can scarcely meet
above twice a year.

01:08:55.256 --> 01:08:57.475
[ Mrs. Jennings Chattering ]

01:08:57.550 --> 01:09:00.144
You seem out of sorts, Miss Dashwood.
Are you quite well?

01:09:00.219 --> 01:09:03.143
Perfectly well. Thank you.
l've not offended you?

01:09:03.221 --> 01:09:06.145
On the contrary. [ Mrs. Jennings]
I cannot stand it any longer.

01:09:06.225 --> 01:09:08.102
I must know what
you're saying, Lucy.

01:09:08.185 --> 01:09:12.612
If anyone finds out, it will ruin him.
Promise me you'll not tell a soul.

01:09:12.689 --> 01:09:14.738
Miss Dashwood
is quite engrossed.

01:09:14.817 --> 01:09:18.242
- [ Charlotte ] You're allowed no secrets
from us, Miss Lucy. - I give you my word.

01:09:19.572 --> 01:09:23.577
V\/ell, and what can have fascinated
you to such an extent, Miss Dashwood?

01:09:23.660 --> 01:09:27.038
- Tell us all!
- VVe were talking of London, ma'am.

01:09:27.121 --> 01:09:29.749
And of all
its diversions.

01:09:29.832 --> 01:09:32.381
Do you hear that, Charlotte?
[Panfing]

01:09:32.460 --> 01:09:35.760
While you were so busy whispering,
Charlotte and I have concocted a plan.

01:09:35.837 --> 01:09:37.840
It is the best plan in the world!

01:09:37.924 --> 01:09:42.520
I make for London shortly,
and I invite you, Lucy...

01:09:42.595 --> 01:09:45.689
and both the Misses Dashwood
to join me.

01:09:45.765 --> 01:09:48.188
[ Sir John ] Splendid idea!
London?

01:09:48.267 --> 01:09:50.144
[Charlotte Giggling ]
lsn't is splendid?

01:09:50.228 --> 01:09:51.729
Can I g0?
Can I g0?

01:09:51.813 --> 01:09:54.066
You know perfectly well
you're too young, dearest.

01:09:54.148 --> 01:09:58.028
I shall convey you all to my house in Chelsea,
and we will taste the delights of the season.

01:09:58.111 --> 01:09:59.533
What say you?

01:09:59.612 --> 01:10:02.365
[ Margaret] Oh, please, can I go?
l'm 12 soon.

01:10:02.448 --> 01:10:06.578
Mr. Palmer, do you not long to have
the Misses Dashwood come to London?

01:10:06.661 --> 01:10:09.665
I came into Devonshire
with no other view.

01:10:10.748 --> 01:10:13.046
Mrs. Jennings,
you are very kind,

01:10:13.126 --> 01:10:14.719
but we cannot possibly
leave our mother.

01:10:14.794 --> 01:10:17.388
Oh, your mother can
spare you very well!

01:10:17.463 --> 01:10:20.216
- [ Mrs. Dashwood ] Of course I can!
- Of course she can!

01:10:20.299 --> 01:10:23.724
I could not be more delighted.
lt is exactly what I would wish.

01:10:23.803 --> 01:10:26.727
[ Mrs. Jennings ] I will brook
no refusal, Miss Dashwood.

01:10:26.806 --> 01:10:29.229
Let us strike hands
on the bargain.

01:10:29.308 --> 01:10:33.563
And if I do not have the three
of you married by Michaelmas,

01:10:33.646 --> 01:10:36.024
it will not be my fault.

01:10:36.107 --> 01:10:38.951
- [ Giggling ] - [ Marianne ] Mrs.
Jennings!

01:10:39.026 --> 01:10:42.030
[Charlotte Chattering ]

01:10:42.113 --> 01:10:43.706
[ Door Closes ]

01:10:43.781 --> 01:10:46.284
[ Marianne ] I was never so
grateful in all my life...

01:10:46.367 --> 01:10:48.665
as I am to Mrs. Jennings.
Oh, Elinor.

01:10:48.745 --> 01:10:52.170
I shall see Willoughby,
and you will see Edward.

01:10:52.874 --> 01:10:54.547
Are you asleep?

01:10:56.085 --> 01:10:59.259
With you in the room?
[ Marianne Sighs ]

01:10:59.338 --> 01:11:03.935
I do not believe you feel as calm
as you look, Elinor. Not even you.

01:11:04.010 --> 01:11:06.980
I will never sleep
tonight.

01:11:07.054 --> 01:11:11.400
V\/hat were you and Miss
Steele talking about so long?

01:11:11.476 --> 01:11:13.899
Nothing of significance.

01:11:16.689 --> 01:11:18.612
[Shouting Farewells]

01:11:18.691 --> 01:11:21.945
[ Marianne ]
You must look after Mama!

01:11:24.071 --> 01:11:27.291
We Will! We will!

01:11:27.366 --> 01:11:30.040
BYE-bye!
GOOd-bye!

01:11:31.496 --> 01:11:34.875
[ Mrs. Jennings ] How do you
think I live poking about...

01:11:34.957 --> 01:11:38.757
in that great house all by myself when I
have been used to having Charlotte...

01:11:38.836 --> 01:11:43.137
until she had the baby? I have
written to Edward, Miss Dashwood.

01:11:43.216 --> 01:11:45.969
And yet I do not know
how much I may see of him.

01:11:46.052 --> 01:11:49.022
Secrecy is vital.
He'll never be able to call.

01:11:49.096 --> 01:11:51.645
I should imagine not.

01:11:51.724 --> 01:11:53.647
It's so hard.

01:11:53.726 --> 01:11:56.696
I believe my only comfort has been
the constancy of his affection.

01:11:56.771 --> 01:11:59.570
You're fortunate, over
such a lengthy engagement,

01:11:59.649 --> 01:12:02.243
never to have had any
doubts on that score.

01:12:02.318 --> 01:12:05.117
Oh. I'm of rather
a jealous nature.

01:12:05.196 --> 01:12:09.167
And if he talked more of one
young woman than any other-

01:12:09.242 --> 01:12:12.712
But he's never given a
momenfs alarm on that count.

01:12:14.330 --> 01:12:17.925
Imagine how glad he'll be
to learn that we are friends.

01:12:24.340 --> 01:12:27.514
There you are, Pigeon. Have you missed me?
Very much, ma'am.

01:12:27.593 --> 01:12:29.687
You always say so,
and I never believe you.

01:12:29.762 --> 01:12:31.856
I trust everything's in order.
In good order, ma'am.

01:12:31.931 --> 01:12:35.435
Though if I might suggest the ordering
of coal- Don't talk to me of coals.

01:12:35.518 --> 01:12:38.271
There you are, Pooter.
Still alive, I see?

01:12:38.354 --> 01:12:40.277
Tea, Pigeon, tea.
Yes, ma'am.

01:12:40.356 --> 01:12:42.199
Ah, then, my dears.
[Whispering ]

01:12:42.275 --> 01:12:44.698
Well, you do not waste
any time, Miss Marianne.

01:12:44.777 --> 01:12:47.371
Give it to Pigeon there.
He'll see to it.

01:12:47.446 --> 01:12:51.292
Come along, dear. A letter. So
they're definitely engaged.

01:12:51.367 --> 01:12:54.120
Mrs. Jennings says your sister will
buy her wedding clothes here in town.

01:12:54.203 --> 01:12:56.956
Dear Miss Steele,
I know of no such plan.

01:12:58.583 --> 01:13:03.089
John and Fanny are in town. I think
we shall be forced to see them.

01:13:06.799 --> 01:13:09.302
I see.
[ Knocking ]

01:13:12.430 --> 01:13:16.355
I think it was for next door.
Yes, you're right.

01:13:16.434 --> 01:13:19.904
Marianne, do sit down
for two seconds together.

01:13:19.979 --> 01:13:22.152
You're making me nervous.

01:13:23.482 --> 01:13:25.951
[ Knocking ]

01:13:28.279 --> 01:13:30.452
[ Maid ] Good afternoon, sir.
[ Man ] Good afternoon.

01:13:30.531 --> 01:13:32.954
Is Miss Marianne here?

01:13:33.034 --> 01:13:36.413
Shh. [ Maid ] VVho shall
I say is calling?

01:13:36.495 --> 01:13:38.623
Very good, sir.

01:13:38.706 --> 01:13:41.175
Oh, Elinor,
it is Willoughby.

01:13:42.376 --> 01:13:44.344
Indeed, it is.

01:13:49.258 --> 01:13:51.727
Oh!

01:13:51.802 --> 01:13:53.725
Excuse me, Colonel.

01:13:54.597 --> 01:13:56.520
Um, Colonel.

01:13:59.060 --> 01:14:03.110
What a pleasure to see you. Have
you been in London all this while?

01:14:03.189 --> 01:14:06.614
Forgive me, Miss Dashwood.

01:14:08.027 --> 01:14:12.032
I have heard reports
through town that-

01:14:14.450 --> 01:14:19.001
Miss Dashwood,
tell me once and for all.

01:14:19.080 --> 01:14:23.836
Is everything finally resolved between
your sister and Mr. Vvilloughby?

01:14:26.712 --> 01:14:29.636
Colonel, though neither one
has informed me...

01:14:29.715 --> 01:14:32.514
of their understanding,

01:14:32.593 --> 01:14:36.268
I have no doubt
of their mutual affection.

01:14:38.307 --> 01:14:40.730
Thank you, Miss Dashwood.

01:14:42.812 --> 01:14:46.533
To your sister,
I wish all imaginable happiness.

01:14:47.733 --> 01:14:52.159
To Mr. Willoughby,
that he may endeavor...

01:14:52.238 --> 01:14:54.081
to deserve her.

01:14:55.241 --> 01:14:57.164
What do you mean?

01:14:59.954 --> 01:15:01.922
Forgive me, I-

01:15:06.168 --> 01:15:08.091
Forgive me.

01:15:09.755 --> 01:15:11.757
[ Door Closes ]

01:15:14.051 --> 01:15:18.557
[ Loud Chattering ]

01:15:20.933 --> 01:15:24.312
Where is dear Edward, John?
We expect to see him daily.

01:15:24.395 --> 01:15:27.399
VVho is “dear Edward,” may I ask?
VVho, indeed?

01:15:27.481 --> 01:15:30.701
My brother, Mrs. Jennings.
Mr. Edward Ferrars.

01:15:30.776 --> 01:15:32.699
Indeed!

01:15:32.778 --> 01:15:35.201
Is that Ferrars
with an “F”?

01:15:35.281 --> 01:15:37.158
[Giggling ]

01:15:41.120 --> 01:15:43.839
No. Are there any
messages, Pigeon?

01:15:43.914 --> 01:15:47.259
No messages at all? No cards?
None, madam.

01:15:47.334 --> 01:15:50.429
I notice you do not inquire
for your messages, Miss Dashwood.

01:15:50.504 --> 01:15:52.848
No, indeed, for I do not
expect any, Mrs. Jennings.

01:15:52.923 --> 01:15:55.346
I have no- very little
acquaintance in town.

01:16:12.860 --> 01:16:16.034
I don't want to hear another
word about the ham bone, Pigeon.

01:16:16.113 --> 01:16:18.957
You and Cartwright must
sort that out between you.

01:16:19.033 --> 01:16:21.502
No messages, ma'am.

01:16:21.577 --> 01:16:24.831
Now, do not fret,
my dear.

01:16:24.914 --> 01:16:26.916
I have been told that
this good weather...

01:16:26.999 --> 01:16:30.094
is keeping many of our sportsmen
in the country at present.

01:16:30.169 --> 01:16:34.424
But the frost will soon drive them to town.
Depend on it.

01:16:34.507 --> 01:16:37.306
Of course. I had not
thought of that.

01:16:37.384 --> 01:16:39.637
[Laughs] Thank you, Mrs.
Jennings.

01:16:39.720 --> 01:16:42.439
And Miss Dashwood may
set her heart at rest,

01:16:42.515 --> 01:16:46.236
for I overheard your sister-in-law say
she is to invite the elusive Mr. F...

01:16:46.310 --> 01:16:48.233
to the ball tonight.

01:16:48.312 --> 01:16:51.031
[ Mrs. Jennings ]
Do be careful, dears.

01:16:51.107 --> 01:16:53.201
The horses have been here.

01:16:53.275 --> 01:16:56.529
Careful. lt's beginning
to rain also.

01:16:56.612 --> 01:16:58.535
Now follow me.

01:17:02.284 --> 01:17:04.878
[ Horse Snorts]
Vvhoops.

01:17:10.543 --> 01:17:14.047
[ People Chattering ]
N' [Orchestral ]

01:17:14.130 --> 01:17:16.053
[ Man ]
Steady!

01:17:16.132 --> 01:17:18.476
No,no,no,no,no.
This is madness.

01:17:18.551 --> 01:17:20.724
This is dribbling,
babbling madness!

01:17:20.803 --> 01:17:24.558
[Chattering ]

01:17:27.768 --> 01:17:29.395
Mama!

01:17:29.478 --> 01:17:32.573
This is very merry!
Charlotte!

01:17:33.315 --> 01:17:36.319
Oh, do you spy anyone we know?
Not a soul.

01:17:36.402 --> 01:17:38.575
Ask Mr. Palmer to look.
He has a better view.

01:17:38.654 --> 01:17:42.158
Mr. Palmer, do you see
anyone of our acquaintance?

01:17:42.241 --> 01:17:45.836
Unfortunately not. How can you
be such a tease, Mr. Palmer?

01:17:45.911 --> 01:17:49.506
There is Mrs. John Dashwood. I can
see her for myself. Mrs. Dashwood!

01:17:49.582 --> 01:17:51.550
Hello!

01:17:52.626 --> 01:17:55.254
Come along, my dears.

01:17:58.883 --> 01:18:01.807
There you are!

01:18:01.886 --> 01:18:04.605
Mrs. Jennings. Oh, goodness.
How hot it is.

01:18:04.680 --> 01:18:06.853
Indeed. You're not
alone, I trust?

01:18:06.932 --> 01:18:09.651
Indeed,no. John is just
gone to fetch my brother.

01:18:09.727 --> 01:18:11.650
They've been
eating ices.

01:18:11.729 --> 01:18:16.951
Your brother! I declare.
This is good news, indeed.

01:18:17.026 --> 01:18:21.202
At long last! Miss Dashwood, I
declare I shall faint clean away.

01:18:21.280 --> 01:18:23.374
Oh, Mrs. Jennings,
I am pleased to see you.

01:18:23.449 --> 01:18:26.453
May I present
my brother-in-law,

01:18:26.535 --> 01:18:28.879
Mr. Robert Ferrars.

01:18:28.954 --> 01:18:30.456
[ Sighs ]

01:18:30.539 --> 01:18:34.009
Um, Miss Dashwood,
Miss Steele, Miss Marianne.

01:18:35.294 --> 01:18:39.265
My dear ladies,
we meet at last.

01:18:41.467 --> 01:18:45.062
[ Mrs. Jennings] So you must be the
younger brother. ls Mr. Edward not here?

01:18:45.137 --> 01:18:47.231
Miss Dashwood here
was counting on him.

01:18:47.306 --> 01:18:50.230
Oh, he's far too busy
for such gatherings...

01:18:50.309 --> 01:18:54.189
and has no special acquaintance here
to make his attendance worthwhile.

01:18:54.271 --> 01:18:59.368
[Laughs] I declare. I do not know what
the young men are about these days.

01:18:59.443 --> 01:19:02.743
Are they all in hiding?
Come, Mr. Robert.

01:19:02.821 --> 01:19:07.292
In the absence of your brother, you must
dance with our lovely Miss Dashwood here.

01:19:12.498 --> 01:19:15.468
It would be my honor.

01:19:20.547 --> 01:19:22.595
And perhaps Miss Steele...

01:19:22.675 --> 01:19:25.895
might consider reserving
the allemande.

01:19:30.140 --> 01:19:34.111
N' [Orchestral ]

01:19:34.186 --> 01:19:36.655
[Woman Laughing ]

01:20:07.052 --> 01:20:10.101
You reside in Devonshire,
I believe, Miss Dashwood?

01:20:10.180 --> 01:20:12.103
Yes.

01:20:14.310 --> 01:20:15.812
In a cottage?

01:20:16.520 --> 01:20:18.443
Yes.

01:20:19.648 --> 01:20:22.948
I am excessively fond
of a cottage.

01:20:25.237 --> 01:20:28.958
If I had any money to spare,
I should build one myself.

01:20:41.754 --> 01:20:43.677
Mr. Willoughby.

01:20:43.756 --> 01:20:45.929
How do you do,
Miss Dashwood?

01:20:46.008 --> 01:20:48.557
L'm very well.
Thank you.

01:20:48.635 --> 01:20:52.139
How's your family?
They're all extremely well,

01:20:52.222 --> 01:20:54.771
Mr. Willoughby.

01:20:54.850 --> 01:20:57.524
Thank you for
your kind inquiry.

01:20:57.603 --> 01:21:00.197
<i>U</i> [ Ends]

01:21:00.272 --> 01:21:02.775
Vvmoughby!

01:21:02.858 --> 01:21:05.862
[ Conversation Stops ]
[Woman #1 ] VVho is she?

01:21:05.944 --> 01:21:08.697
[Woman #2 ]
She came in with Mrs. Jennings.

01:21:08.781 --> 01:21:10.579
[Woman #3 ]
Mrs. John Dashwood.

01:21:13.202 --> 01:21:15.125
Good God, Willoughby.

01:21:18.665 --> 01:21:21.043
Will you not
shake hands with me?

01:21:22.628 --> 01:21:24.551
How do you do,
Miss Marianne?

01:21:28.008 --> 01:21:30.056
Vvmoughby,
what is the matter?

01:21:30.135 --> 01:21:33.059
Why have you not
come to see me?

01:21:33.138 --> 01:21:37.985
V\/ere you not in London? Have
you not received my letters?

01:21:38.060 --> 01:21:42.987
Yes, I had the pleasure of receiving the
information you were so good as to send me.

01:21:43.065 --> 01:21:47.696
II [ Resumes ] For
heaven's sake, Vvmoughby,

01:21:47.778 --> 01:21:49.701
tell me what is wrong.

01:21:51.907 --> 01:21:54.330
Thank you.
l'm most obliged.

01:21:55.744 --> 01:21:58.418
If you will excuse me,
I must rejoin my party.

01:22:04.920 --> 01:22:06.513
[ Mouths Words ]

01:22:11.176 --> 01:22:13.144
[ Man ]
Ah, Willoughby.

01:22:20.394 --> 01:22:24.115
Go to him, Elinor. Force him
to come to me instantly.

01:22:24.189 --> 01:22:26.942
[ Elinor] Marianne, you
must- you must come away.

01:22:30.195 --> 01:22:33.039
[Woman ]
Do you know them?

01:22:33.115 --> 01:22:36.119
Acquaintances
from the country.

01:22:37.578 --> 01:22:39.706
Indeed.

01:22:39.788 --> 01:22:42.632
[Woman #2 ] Vveafingthek
country fashions, I see.

01:22:45.210 --> 01:22:47.463
Come away, dearest.

01:22:47.546 --> 01:22:49.548
Come away.

01:22:56.096 --> 01:22:59.350
I do not understand. I must speak to him.
I must go to him.

01:22:59.433 --> 01:23:01.310
[ Mrs. Jennings ]
There you are, my dear!

01:23:01.393 --> 01:23:03.896
Oh, my goodness. Come, dear.
[Whispering ]

01:23:03.979 --> 01:23:05.902
You need some air.

01:23:11.153 --> 01:23:13.076
[Woman ]
She called out his name.

01:23:13.155 --> 01:23:15.078
[ Man ] John Dashwood's sisters.

01:23:19.161 --> 01:23:22.085
Lucy! Lucy, come, dear.
We must go.

01:23:22.164 --> 01:23:24.667
VVe're leaving so soon? If I
might be so bold, Mrs. Jennings,

01:23:24.750 --> 01:23:27.173
it would be our pleasure to
escort your young charge home.

01:23:27.252 --> 01:23:30.301
Oh, how very kind. That
is very handsome ofyou.

01:23:31.089 --> 01:23:34.844
She actually sent him messages
during the night? Yes, indeed.

01:23:34.927 --> 01:23:38.056
[Lucy] Mr. Pigeon was
not himself all day.

01:23:47.022 --> 01:23:49.195
Marianne,
please tell me.

01:23:49.274 --> 01:23:51.777
Do not ask me questions.

01:23:51.860 --> 01:23:54.409
You have
no confidence in me.

01:23:54.488 --> 01:23:58.584
This reproach from you?
You who confide in no one?

01:24:00.369 --> 01:24:02.371
I have nothing to tell.

01:24:02.454 --> 01:24:05.833
Nor I. Neither of us
have anything to tell.

01:24:05.916 --> 01:24:09.921
I, because I conceal nothing and you,
because you communicate nothing.

01:24:17.803 --> 01:24:20.898
[ Mrs. Jennings] I wish Lady Charteris
would limit her invitation list.

01:24:20.973 --> 01:24:23.567
I do not know when
l've been so warm.

01:24:23.642 --> 01:24:26.691
L'm glad we left early.

01:24:26.770 --> 01:24:29.193
There, now.

01:24:33.610 --> 01:24:38.207
[ Chuckling ] Lovers'
quarrels are swift to heal.

01:24:38.282 --> 01:24:42.662
That letter will do the trick. Mark
my words. VVell, I must be off.

01:24:42.744 --> 01:24:47.716
I do hope he doesn't keep her
waiting much longer, Miss Dashwood.

01:24:47.791 --> 01:24:50.761
It hurts to see her
looking so forlorn.

01:24:50.836 --> 01:24:53.089
[ Mrs. Jennings]
Pigeon. Pigeon!

01:24:53.171 --> 01:24:56.892
What a welcome I had from
Edwards family, Miss Dashwood.

01:24:56.967 --> 01:25:00.892
L'm surprised you never mentioned how
agreeable your sister-in-law is.

01:25:00.971 --> 01:25:03.565
And Mr. Robert-
all so affable.

01:25:03.640 --> 01:25:06.940
It is perhaps fortunate that none
of them knows of your engagement.

01:25:07.019 --> 01:25:08.987
Excuse me.

01:25:17.738 --> 01:25:20.082
“My dear madam,

01:25:20.157 --> 01:25:25.004
l'm quite at a loss to discover in what point
I could be so unfortunate as to offend you.

01:25:25.078 --> 01:25:27.251
My esteem for your family
is very sincere,

01:25:27.331 --> 01:25:31.086
but if I have given rise to a belief of
more than I felt or meant to express,

01:25:31.168 --> 01:25:35.093
I shall reproach myself for
not having been more guarded.

01:25:35.172 --> 01:25:38.016
My affections have long
been engaged elsewhere,

01:25:38.091 --> 01:25:41.470
and it is with great regret that I return
your letters and the lock of hair...

01:25:41.553 --> 01:25:44.147
which you so obligingly
bestowed upon me.

01:25:44.222 --> 01:25:46.816
I am, et cetera,
John Willoughby.”

01:25:46.892 --> 01:25:48.815
Oh, Marianne.

01:25:51.271 --> 01:25:53.239
Dearest.

01:25:55.942 --> 01:25:58.570
It is best to know what
his intentions are at once.

01:25:58.654 --> 01:26:02.158
Think of what you would have felt if your
engagement had carried on for months and months...

01:26:02.240 --> 01:26:04.208
before he chose
to put an end to it.

01:26:04.284 --> 01:26:06.753
We're not engaged.

01:26:06.828 --> 01:26:08.580
But y-you wrote to him.

01:26:08.664 --> 01:26:11.884
I thought that he must have left you
with some kind of understanding.

01:26:11.958 --> 01:26:15.553
No. He's not so unworthy
as you think him.

01:26:15.629 --> 01:26:19.224
Not so unworthy? Did he
tell you that he loved you?

01:26:19.299 --> 01:26:21.893
Yes.

01:26:21.968 --> 01:26:25.063
No. Never absolutely.

01:26:25.138 --> 01:26:28.062
It was every day implied,
but never declared.

01:26:28.141 --> 01:26:31.691
Sometimes I thought it had
been, but it never was.

01:26:31.770 --> 01:26:35.525
He has broken no vow. He has!
He's broken faith with all of us.

01:26:35.607 --> 01:26:38.201
He made us all believe
he loved you.

01:26:38.276 --> 01:26:40.199
He did.

01:26:40.278 --> 01:26:43.407
He did. He loved me
as I loved him.

01:26:43.490 --> 01:26:46.289
[Sobbing ]
[ Knocking ]

01:26:46.368 --> 01:26:50.669
I had to come straight up.
How are you, Miss Marianne?

01:26:52.082 --> 01:26:54.551
Oh, poor thing.
She looks very bad.

01:26:54.626 --> 01:26:57.220
'Tis no wonder, Miss Dashwood,
for 'tis but too true.

01:26:57.295 --> 01:27:00.674
I was told in the street here by
Miss Morton, a very great friend,

01:27:00.757 --> 01:27:05.558
he is to be married at the end of the
month to a Miss Grey with £50,000.

01:27:05.637 --> 01:27:09.892
Well, said I, if 'tis true,
then he is a good-for-nothing...

01:27:09.975 --> 01:27:12.444
who's used my young friend
abominably ill.

01:27:12.519 --> 01:27:15.398
And I wish with all my soul that his
wife might plague his heart out.

01:27:15.480 --> 01:27:16.948
[Sobbing Continues]

01:27:17.023 --> 01:27:19.822
Oh. Oh, my dear.

01:27:19.901 --> 01:27:22.905
He's not the only
young man worth having.

01:27:22.988 --> 01:27:26.834
With your pretty face, you'll
never want for admirers.

01:27:27.492 --> 01:27:30.211
There.

01:27:30.287 --> 01:27:33.541
Better let her have her cry out
and have done with it.

01:27:33.623 --> 01:27:35.500
Mmm.

01:27:35.584 --> 01:27:38.337
I will go look out
something to tempt her.

01:27:40.130 --> 01:27:42.053
Does she care for olives?

01:27:43.884 --> 01:27:45.807
I cannot tell you.

01:27:46.470 --> 01:27:48.472
[ Mouths Words ]

01:27:53.351 --> 01:27:56.195
Apparently,
they never were engaged.

01:27:56.271 --> 01:28:00.492
Miss Grey has £50,000.
Marianne is virtually penniless.

01:28:00.567 --> 01:28:03.787
She cannot have expected
him to go through with it.

01:28:03.862 --> 01:28:05.956
But I feel for Marianne.

01:28:06.031 --> 01:28:09.581
She will lose her bloom and
end a spinster, like Elinor.

01:28:11.077 --> 01:28:15.173
I think, my dear, we might consider having
them to stay with us for a few days.

01:28:15.248 --> 01:28:19.094
VVe are, after all, family.
And my father- My love.

01:28:20.170 --> 01:28:23.140
I would ask them
with all my head, but...

01:28:23.215 --> 01:28:26.219
l've already asked
Miss Steele for a visit.

01:28:26.301 --> 01:28:30.522
And we cannot deprive Mrs. Jennings
of all her company at once.

01:28:30.597 --> 01:28:33.897
We can invite your sisters
some other year, you know.

01:28:33.975 --> 01:28:37.821
And Miss Steele will profit far
more from your generosity.

01:28:37.896 --> 01:28:41.070
Poor girl.
Excellent notion.

01:28:44.069 --> 01:28:46.413
[ Knocking ]

01:28:46.488 --> 01:28:49.082
[ Maid ] Colonel Brandon
to see you, Miss Dashwood.

01:28:49.157 --> 01:28:51.080
Colonel.

01:28:52.202 --> 01:28:54.830
Thank you so much
for coming.

01:28:54.913 --> 01:28:57.166
How is your sister?

01:28:57.249 --> 01:28:59.593
I must get her home
as quickly as possible.

01:28:59.668 --> 01:29:02.672
The Palmers can take us <i>as</i> far
as their home at Cleveland,

01:29:02.754 --> 01:29:04.381
which is but a day
from Barton.

01:29:04.464 --> 01:29:09.140
Then permit me to accompany you and take you
straight on from Cleveland to Barton myself.

01:29:09.219 --> 01:29:11.813
I confess that is precisely
what I had hoped for.

01:29:12.889 --> 01:29:14.812
Marianne suffers cruelly.

01:29:16.685 --> 01:29:20.861
V\/hat pains me most is how hard she
tries to justify Mr. VVilloughby.

01:29:20.939 --> 01:29:23.738
But you know
her disposition.

01:29:27.237 --> 01:29:30.867
Perhaps... I-

01:29:30.949 --> 01:29:33.702
Miss Dashwood,
would you allow me...

01:29:33.785 --> 01:29:38.211
to relate some circumstances which nothing
but an earnest desire of being useful-

01:29:38.290 --> 01:29:41.385
You have something to tell me
of Mr. Willoughby?

01:29:52.012 --> 01:29:55.892
When I quitted Barton last-

01:29:55.974 --> 01:29:58.602
No, I must go further back.

01:29:59.811 --> 01:30:03.065
No doubt-

01:30:03.148 --> 01:30:06.402
No doubt, Mrs. Jennings
has apprised you...

01:30:06.484 --> 01:30:09.738
of certain events in my past.

01:30:09.821 --> 01:30:13.667
The sad outcome of my connection
with a young woman named Eliza.

01:30:18.163 --> 01:30:20.461
What is not commonly known
is that...

01:30:22.000 --> 01:30:23.923
20 years ago,
before she died,

01:30:24.002 --> 01:30:27.131
Eliza bore
an illegitimate child.

01:30:28.340 --> 01:30:31.389
The father, whoever he was,
abandoned them.

01:30:32.677 --> 01:30:35.430
As Eliza lay dying,

01:30:35.513 --> 01:30:38.767
she begged me
to look after the child.

01:30:38.850 --> 01:30:40.944
I had failed Eliza
in every other way.

01:30:41.019 --> 01:30:44.273
I could not refuse her now.

01:30:44.356 --> 01:30:47.951
I took the child-
Beth is her name-

01:30:48.026 --> 01:30:52.873
and placed her with a family in the country where I
could be sure that she would be well looked after.

01:30:52.948 --> 01:30:54.621
I saw her whenever I could.

01:30:54.699 --> 01:30:58.875
And she grew up
so headstrong.

01:30:58.954 --> 01:31:01.753
And God forgive me,
I indulged her.

01:31:01.831 --> 01:31:05.506
I allowed her
too much freedom.

01:31:05.585 --> 01:31:07.963
Almost a year ago,
she disappeared.

01:31:08.046 --> 01:31:10.640
Disappeared?
I instigated a search,

01:31:10.715 --> 01:31:13.764
but for eight months I was
left to imagine the worst.

01:31:13.843 --> 01:31:16.722
At last, on the day
of the Delaford picnic,

01:31:16.805 --> 01:31:19.934
I received the first news
ofhen

01:31:21.184 --> 01:31:24.313
She was with child.

01:31:25.689 --> 01:31:31.492
And the blackguard who had left her
with no hint of his whereabouts-

01:31:31.569 --> 01:31:33.867
Oh, good God.

01:31:37.575 --> 01:31:39.498
Do you mean Willoughby?

01:31:43.456 --> 01:31:45.333
Before I could
return to confront him,

01:31:45.417 --> 01:31:49.012
Lady Allen had learned of his behavior
and turned him from the house.

01:31:49.087 --> 01:31:53.888
He fled to London. Yes, he left us
that morning without any explanation.

01:31:53.967 --> 01:31:56.311
Lady Allen
had annulled his legacy.

01:31:56.386 --> 01:31:59.731
He was left with next to nothing and
in danger of losing Combe Magna...

01:31:59.806 --> 01:32:02.025
and all the money that
remained to his debtors.

01:32:03.268 --> 01:32:06.488
So he abandoned Marianne...

01:32:06.563 --> 01:32:09.066
for Miss Grey
and her £50,000.

01:32:13.611 --> 01:32:16.285
Is Beth still in town?

01:32:16.364 --> 01:32:21.211
She has chosen to return to the
country for her confinement.

01:32:22.412 --> 01:32:24.335
[ Sighs ]

01:32:28.126 --> 01:32:31.050
I would not have burdened you,
Miss Dashwood,

01:32:31.129 --> 01:32:33.052
had I not, from my heart,

01:32:33.131 --> 01:32:35.225
believed it might in time...

01:32:35.300 --> 01:32:38.554
lessen your sister's regrets.

01:32:48.313 --> 01:32:50.862
I have described
Mr. Willoughby...

01:32:50.940 --> 01:32:54.570
as the worst of libertines.

01:32:54.652 --> 01:32:56.905
But I have since learned
from Lady Allen...

01:32:56.988 --> 01:33:00.242
that he did mean to propose
that day, and therefore,

01:33:00.325 --> 01:33:04.580
lcannotdeny that his
intentions towards Marianne...

01:33:04.662 --> 01:33:07.006
were honorable.

01:33:07.082 --> 01:33:09.005
And...

01:33:10.251 --> 01:33:14.722
I feel certain that
he would have married her...

01:33:14.798 --> 01:33:16.721
had it not been-

01:33:16.800 --> 01:33:19.599
For the money.

01:33:24.766 --> 01:33:27.940
Dearest, was I right
to tell you?

01:33:28.019 --> 01:33:29.942
Of course.

01:33:32.690 --> 01:33:35.284
Whatever his past actions,

01:33:35.360 --> 01:33:37.533
whatever his present course,

01:33:37.612 --> 01:33:40.786
at least you may be certain
that he loved you.

01:33:42.492 --> 01:33:44.415
Butnotenough.

01:33:46.037 --> 01:33:47.960
Notenough.

01:33:54.420 --> 01:33:56.639
[ Door Opens ]

01:33:56.714 --> 01:34:00.890
Here is someone to cheer
you up, Miss Dashwood.

01:34:00.969 --> 01:34:02.642
[ Mrs. Jennings
Chuckling ]

01:34:03.805 --> 01:34:08.481
Oh, how is your dear sister,
Miss Dashwood?

01:34:08.560 --> 01:34:10.562
Poor thing.

01:34:10.645 --> 01:34:15.401
I must say, I do not know what I should do
if a man treated me with so little respect.

01:34:15.483 --> 01:34:18.453
How are you enjoying your stay
with John and Fanny, Miss Steele?

01:34:18.528 --> 01:34:21.998
Oh, I was never so happy in my
entire life, Miss Dashwood.

01:34:22.073 --> 01:34:25.327
I do believe your sister-in-law
has taken quite a fancy to me.

01:34:25.410 --> 01:34:29.415
Oh, I had to come and tell you, for
you cannot imagine what has happened.

01:34:29.497 --> 01:34:34.253
No,lcannoL Yesterday, I was
introduced to Edward's mother.

01:34:35.253 --> 01:34:38.006
And she was a vast deal
more than civil.

01:34:38.089 --> 01:34:40.012
I have not yet seen Edward,

01:34:40.091 --> 01:34:42.059
but I feel sure to very soon.

01:34:42.135 --> 01:34:44.058
[ Knocking ]
Come in.

01:34:46.931 --> 01:34:50.777
There's a Mr. Edward Ferrars
to see you, Miss Dashwood.

01:34:52.812 --> 01:34:55.486
Oh.

01:34:55.565 --> 01:34:58.614
Do ask him to come in.

01:35:03.489 --> 01:35:05.457
[ Maid ]
This way, sir.

01:35:23.051 --> 01:35:25.349
Mr. Ferrars.

01:35:25.428 --> 01:35:27.601
Miss Dashwood.

01:35:33.811 --> 01:35:35.813
What a pleasure to see you.

01:35:35.897 --> 01:35:38.696
- Miss Dashwood, how can l- - You
know Miss Steele, of course.

01:35:44.530 --> 01:35:47.909
Indeed. How do you do,
Miss Steele?

01:35:47.992 --> 01:35:50.791
I am well, thank you,
Mr. Ferrars.

01:35:51.996 --> 01:35:54.465
Do sit down.

01:35:57.502 --> 01:36:00.096
Thank you.
[ Swallows ] Yes.

01:36:01.965 --> 01:36:05.060
You must be surprised
to find me here, Mr. Ferrars.

01:36:05.134 --> 01:36:07.887
I expect you thought I was
at your sister's house.

01:36:09.347 --> 01:36:11.270
Let me fetch Marianne.

01:36:11.349 --> 01:36:14.819
- Mr. Ferrars, she would be most disappointed
to miss you. - [ Marianne ] Edward?

01:36:15.895 --> 01:36:18.648
Edward,
I heard your voice.

01:36:19.899 --> 01:36:22.152
At last, you've found us.

01:36:22.235 --> 01:36:25.830
Forgive me, Marianne. My
visit is shamefully overdue.

01:36:25.905 --> 01:36:29.409
You're pale. Y0u've not
been unwell, lhope.

01:36:29.492 --> 01:36:32.962
Do not think of me.
Elinor is well, you see.

01:36:33.037 --> 01:36:35.631
That must be enough
for both of us.

01:36:35.707 --> 01:36:39.211
L-lndeed. And h-how do you
enjoy London, Miss Marianne?

01:36:39.294 --> 01:36:43.140
Not at all. The sight of you is
all the pleasure it has afforded.

01:36:43.214 --> 01:36:45.592
Is that not so, Elinor?

01:36:47.510 --> 01:36:49.933
Why have you not
come to see us before?

01:36:50.013 --> 01:36:52.983
I have been
much engaged elsewhere.

01:36:53.057 --> 01:36:55.526
Engaged elsewhere?

01:36:55.601 --> 01:36:58.024
But what was that when there
were such friends to be met?

01:36:58.104 --> 01:37:01.608
Perhaps, Miss Marianne, you think young men
never honor their engagements, little or great.

01:37:01.691 --> 01:37:07.243
No, indeed. For Edward is the most incapable
of being selfish of anyone I ever saw.

01:37:11.075 --> 01:37:13.828
Edward, will you not sit?

01:37:13.911 --> 01:37:16.585
Elinor, help me
to persuade him.

01:37:25.590 --> 01:37:28.389
Forgive me. Forgive me.
l-l must take my leave.

01:37:28.468 --> 01:37:29.970
You're only just arrived.

01:37:30.053 --> 01:37:34.433
You would excuse me, but I, um, have an urgent
commission to attend to on Fanny's behalf.

01:37:34.515 --> 01:37:38.736
In that case, perhaps you might escort me
back to your sister's house, Mr. Ferrars.

01:37:41.647 --> 01:37:43.775
It would be an honor.

01:37:46.402 --> 01:37:48.575
Miss Dashwood.

01:37:48.654 --> 01:37:50.622
Marianne.

01:38:04.128 --> 01:38:07.632
Why did you not
urge him to stay?

01:38:07.715 --> 01:38:10.468
He must have had
his reasons for going.

01:38:10.551 --> 01:38:13.225
His reason was, no doubt,
your coldness.

01:38:13.304 --> 01:38:17.229
If I were Edward, I would assume
you did not care for me at all.

01:38:21.145 --> 01:38:24.399
[Lucy] Poor Miss Marianne looked
very badly the other day.

01:38:24.482 --> 01:38:27.861
VVhen I think of her, it frightens me
to think that I shall never marry.

01:38:27.944 --> 01:38:31.619
Nonsense. You will marry far better
than either of the Dashwood girls.

01:38:32.990 --> 01:38:36.244
Oh, but I have no dowry.

01:38:36.327 --> 01:38:39.080
There are qualities which
will always make up for that,

01:38:39.163 --> 01:38:42.087
and you have them
in abundance.

01:38:42.166 --> 01:38:45.386
It would not surprise me if you
were to marry far and away...

01:38:45.461 --> 01:38:47.384
beyond your expectations.

01:38:47.463 --> 01:38:49.886
Oh, I wish that
might be so.

01:38:52.176 --> 01:38:55.430
There is a young man.

01:38:55.513 --> 01:38:58.187
Aha.
l'm glad to hear of it.

01:38:58.266 --> 01:39:00.689
Is he of good fortune
and breeding?

01:39:00.768 --> 01:39:02.691
Of both.

01:39:02.770 --> 01:39:06.525
B-But his family would
certainly oppose the match.

01:39:06.607 --> 01:39:11.283
Tush. They will allow it as
soon as they see you, my dear.

01:39:11.362 --> 01:39:14.536
It is a very great secret.

01:39:14.615 --> 01:39:18.665
L've told nobody in the world
for fear of discovery.

01:39:19.745 --> 01:39:22.749
I am the soul of discretion.

01:39:23.875 --> 01:39:26.253
If I dared tell-

01:39:27.879 --> 01:39:32.225
I can assure you,
I am as silent as the grave.

01:39:37.138 --> 01:39:39.891
[ Whispering ] lt's
your brother Edward.

01:39:39.974 --> 01:39:43.148
Viper in my bosom!
[Squealing ]

01:39:43.227 --> 01:39:46.231
[Screaming ]
Get out!

01:39:46.314 --> 01:39:48.362
[Whimpering ]
Stop this! Stop this!

01:39:48.441 --> 01:39:50.489
[ Grunting ] Ow! Ow! Get out!

01:39:50.568 --> 01:39:53.412
[ Lucy Screaming ]

01:39:53.488 --> 01:39:55.911
[ Bells Jingling ]

01:40:05.416 --> 01:40:08.420
Oh, my dears.
What a commotion.

01:40:08.503 --> 01:40:12.849
Mr. Edward Ferrars, the very one I
used to joke you about, Miss Dashwood,

01:40:12.924 --> 01:40:17.100
is engaged these five
years to Lucy Steele.

01:40:17.178 --> 01:40:19.180
Poor Mr. Ferrars.

01:40:19.263 --> 01:40:21.607
His mother, who by all
accounts is very proud,

01:40:21.682 --> 01:40:25.778
has demanded that he break the
engagement on pain of disinheritance.

01:40:25.853 --> 01:40:29.232
But he has refused
to break his promise to Lucy.

01:40:29.315 --> 01:40:33.491
He has stood by her, good man,
and is cut off without a penny.

01:40:33.569 --> 01:40:37.199
She has settled it all
irrevocably on Mr. Robert.

01:40:37.281 --> 01:40:40.660
But I cannot stop.
I must go to Lucy.

01:40:40.743 --> 01:40:44.338
Your sister-in-law scolded her like
any fury, drove her to hysteria.

01:40:45.623 --> 01:40:47.796
How long have you known?

01:40:47.875 --> 01:40:50.799
[ Mrs. Jennings] Pigeon, I need
the carriage this instant!

01:40:52.380 --> 01:40:55.384
Since the night Mrs. Jennings
offered to take us to London.

01:40:55.466 --> 01:40:57.844
Why did you not tell me?

01:40:57.927 --> 01:41:01.227
Lucy told me in the
strictest confidence.

01:41:01.305 --> 01:41:03.899
[ Exhales]
I could not break my word.

01:41:03.975 --> 01:41:07.730
- But Edward loves you.
- He made me no promises.

01:41:07.812 --> 01:41:10.816
- He tried to tell me aboutLucy.
- He cannot marry her.

01:41:10.898 --> 01:41:14.573
Would you have him treat her even worse
than Willoughby has treated you?

01:41:14.652 --> 01:41:16.620
N0.

01:41:16.696 --> 01:41:19.290
But nor would I have him
marry where he does not love.

01:41:19.365 --> 01:41:23.415
Edward made his promise a long
time ago, long before he met me.

01:41:23.494 --> 01:41:25.917
Though he may harbor
some r-regret,

01:41:25.997 --> 01:41:30.218
I believe that he will be happy in the knowledge
that he did his duty and kept his word.

01:41:30.293 --> 01:41:32.216
[ Sighs ]
After all-

01:41:32.295 --> 01:41:36.801
After all that
is bewitching...

01:41:36.882 --> 01:41:40.261
intheidea of one's happiness
entirely depending on one person,

01:41:40.344 --> 01:41:42.267
it is not always possible.

01:41:42.346 --> 01:41:44.314
We must accept.

01:41:45.516 --> 01:41:48.360
Edward will marry Lucy.

01:41:48.436 --> 01:41:51.280
And you and I will go home.

01:41:51.355 --> 01:41:54.404
Always resignation
and acceptance.

01:41:54.483 --> 01:41:57.578
Always prudence
and honor and duty.

01:41:58.863 --> 01:42:01.241
Elinor,
where is your heart?

01:42:02.700 --> 01:42:04.919
[ Sighs ] VVhat do you
know of my heart?

01:42:04.994 --> 01:42:07.588
What do you know of anything
but your own suffering?

01:42:07.663 --> 01:42:10.132
For weeks, Marianne,
l've had this pressing on me...

01:42:10.207 --> 01:42:12.926
without being at liberty to speak
of it to a single creature.

01:42:13.002 --> 01:42:18.600
It was forced on me by the very person
whose prior claims ruined all my hopes.

01:42:18.674 --> 01:42:22.679
[ Sighs ] I have endured her
exultation again and again...

01:42:22.762 --> 01:42:25.436
whilst knowing myself
to be divided from Edward forever.

01:42:25.514 --> 01:42:27.937
Believe me, Marianne,
had I not been bound to silence,

01:42:28.017 --> 01:42:31.237
I could have produced proof enough
of a broken heart even for you.

01:42:35.941 --> 01:42:39.161
Elinor.

01:42:39.236 --> 01:42:41.659
[Crying Quietly]

01:42:49.038 --> 01:42:52.042
[ Sobs ]

01:42:55.753 --> 01:42:58.222
Oh!

01:42:58.297 --> 01:43:01.016
[ Brandon ] I have heard that
owing to his engagement,

01:43:01.092 --> 01:43:05.848
your friend Mr. Ferrars has lost his
fortune irrevocably to his brother.

01:43:05.930 --> 01:43:08.729
Have I been rightly informed?
ls it so?

01:43:08.808 --> 01:43:11.903
It is, indeed, so.

01:43:11.977 --> 01:43:15.072
Are you acquainted
with Mr. Ferrars?

01:43:15.147 --> 01:43:19.698
Uh, no,
we have never met.

01:43:19.777 --> 01:43:22.872
But I know only too well
the cruelty-

01:43:24.323 --> 01:43:27.668
the impolitic cruelty
of dividing two young people...

01:43:27.743 --> 01:43:30.166
long attached to one another.

01:43:33.040 --> 01:43:37.546
I have a proposal to make that should enable
him to marry Miss Steele immediately.

01:43:39.422 --> 01:43:42.175
Since the gentleman
is so close a friend to your family,

01:43:42.258 --> 01:43:44.431
perhaps you would be good enough
to mention it to him.

01:43:46.721 --> 01:43:48.723
Oh.

01:43:48.806 --> 01:43:53.607
Colonel, I am sure he would be only too
delighted to hear it from your own lips.

01:43:54.937 --> 01:43:56.860
I think not.

01:43:58.149 --> 01:44:00.902
His behavior
has proved him proud.

01:44:00.985 --> 01:44:03.909
In the best sense.

01:44:06.615 --> 01:44:09.243
I feel certain
this is the right course.

01:44:13.748 --> 01:44:15.921
[ Knocking ]

01:44:16.000 --> 01:44:18.002
[ Maid ]
Mr. Edward Ferrars.

01:44:23.382 --> 01:44:25.601
Mr. Ferrars.

01:44:25.676 --> 01:44:27.599
Miss Dashwood.

01:44:29.013 --> 01:44:32.017
Thank you for responding
so promptly to my message.

01:44:32.099 --> 01:44:34.522
I was most grateful
to receive it.

01:44:36.020 --> 01:44:38.773
Miss Dashwood, God knows
what you must think of me.

01:44:38.856 --> 01:44:41.359
Mr. Ferrars- I have no
right to speak, I know.

01:44:41.442 --> 01:44:46.289
I have- I have good news.
Do please sit down.

01:44:52.620 --> 01:44:56.716
L-l think you know of our
friend, Colonel Brandon.

01:44:56.791 --> 01:44:58.714
Yes, l've heard his name.

01:44:58.793 --> 01:45:01.046
Colonel Brandon
desires me to say...

01:45:01.128 --> 01:45:04.632
that understanding you
wish to join the clergy,

01:45:04.715 --> 01:45:10.063
he has great pleasure in offering you
the parish on his estate at Delaford...

01:45:10.137 --> 01:45:13.562
in the hope that it may enable
you and Miss Steele to marry.

01:45:16.393 --> 01:45:18.395
C-Colonel Brandon?

01:45:18.479 --> 01:45:22.109
Yes. He means it as
testimony of his concern...

01:45:22.191 --> 01:45:25.411
for the cruel situation in
which you now find yourselves.

01:45:28.656 --> 01:45:31.580
Colonel Brandon
give me a parish?

01:45:33.244 --> 01:45:35.167
Can it be possible?

01:45:36.997 --> 01:45:41.924
The unkindness of your family makes you
astonished to find friendship elsewhere.

01:45:44.338 --> 01:45:46.841
N0.

01:45:46.924 --> 01:45:49.848
Not to find it in you.

01:45:49.927 --> 01:45:53.181
I cannot be ignorant that it is
certainly to you that I owe this.

01:45:53.264 --> 01:45:55.187
L'd- I feel it.

01:45:55.266 --> 01:45:57.519
I would express it ifl
could, but, as you know-

01:45:57.601 --> 01:45:59.524
No,no,no.
I am no orator.

01:45:59.603 --> 01:46:02.857
You are mistaken. You owe it
almost entirely to your own merit.

01:46:02.940 --> 01:46:05.409
L've had no hand in it.

01:46:09.738 --> 01:46:13.459
Colonel Brandon must be a man of
great worth and respectability.

01:46:13.534 --> 01:46:16.754
Yes, he is the kindest
and best of men.

01:46:20.875 --> 01:46:25.005
Uh, may I ask why the colonel
did not tell me himself?

01:46:26.463 --> 01:46:31.094
I think he felt it would be
better coming from a friend.

01:46:36.599 --> 01:46:40.524
Your friendship has been the
most important of my life.

01:46:45.316 --> 01:46:47.785
You will always have it.

01:46:52.823 --> 01:46:54.791
Forgive me.

01:46:56.368 --> 01:46:58.291
Mr. Ferrars, you honor
your promises.

01:46:58.370 --> 01:47:01.374
That is more important
than anything else.

01:47:01.457 --> 01:47:05.883
L- I wish you both
very happy.

01:47:12.593 --> 01:47:14.516
Miss Dashwood.

01:47:30.027 --> 01:47:31.995
[ Horse Snorting ]

